P_HTM[1953]="*4. Aniccasuttaṃ**Impermanence*";
P_HTM[1954]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[1955]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[1956]="*“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena dhammaṃ desetu … pe … ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti.**“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”*";
P_HTM[1957]="*“Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, aniccaṃ; tatra te chando pahātabbo”ti.**“Mendicant, give up desire for anything that’s impermanent.”*";
P_HTM[1958]="*“Aññātaṃ, bhagavā, aññātaṃ, sugatā”ti.**“Understood, Blessed One! Understood, Holy One!”*";
