P_HTM[2047]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[2048]="*“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā … pe … vihareyyan”ti.**“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”*";
P_HTM[2049]="*“Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, rajanīyasaṇṭhitaṃ; tatra te chando pahātabbo”ti.**“Mendicant, give up desire for anything that’s stuck in what’s arousing.”*";
P_HTM[2050]="*“Aññātaṃ, bhagavā, aññātaṃ, sugatā”ti.**“Understood, Blessed One! Understood, Holy One!”*";
P_HTM[2051]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāsī”ti?**“But how do you see the detailed meaning of my brief statement?”*";
P_HTM[2052]="*“Rūpaṃ kho, bhante, rajanīyasaṇṭhitaṃ; tatra me chando pahātabbo.**“Sir, form is stuck in what’s arousing; I should give up desire for it.*";
