P_HTM[4497]="*10. Tatiyakoṭṭhikasuttaṃ**With Koṭṭhita (3rd)*";
P_HTM[4498]="*Taññeva nidānaṃ.**The same setting.*";
P_HTM[4499]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ mahākoṭṭhikaṃ etadavoca:**Sāriputta said to Mahākoṭṭhita:*";
P_HTM[4500]="*“‘avijjā, avijjā’ti, āvuso koṭṭhika, vuccati.**“Reverend Koṭṭhita, they speak of this thing called ‘ignorance’.*";
P_HTM[4501]="*Katamā nu kho, āvuso, avijjā;**What is ignorance?*";
P_HTM[4502]="*kittāvatā ca avijjāgato hotī”ti?**And how is an ignorant person defined?”*";
P_HTM[4503]="*“Idhāvuso, assutavā puthujjano rūpaṃ nappajānāti, rūpasamudayaṃ nappajānāti, rūpanirodhaṃ nappajānāti, rūpanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ nappajānāti.**“Reverend, it’s when an uneducated ordinary person doesn’t understand form, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation.*";
P_HTM[4504]="*Vedanaṃ nappajānāti … pe …**They don’t understand feeling …*";
P_HTM[4505]="*saññaṃ …**perception …*";
P_HTM[4506]="*saṅkhāre …**choices …*";
P_HTM[4507]="*viññāṇaṃ nappajānāti, viññāṇasamudayaṃ nappajānāti, viññāṇanirodhaṃ nappajānāti, viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ nappajānāti.**consciousness, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation.*";
P_HTM[4508]="*Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, avijjā;**This is called ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4509]="*ettāvatā ca avijjāgato hotī”ti.**And this is how an ignorant person is defined.”*";
P_HTM[4510]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ mahākoṭṭhikaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Sāriputta said to him:*";
P_HTM[4511]="*“‘vijjā, vijjā’ti, āvuso koṭṭhika, vuccati.**“Reverend Koṭṭhita, they speak of this thing called ‘knowledge’.*";
P_HTM[4512]="*Katamā nu kho, āvuso, vijjā;**What is knowledge?*";
P_HTM[4513]="*kittāvatā ca vijjāgato hotī”ti?**And how is a knowledgeable person defined?”*";
P_HTM[4514]="*“Idhāvuso, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpaṃ pajānāti, rūpasamudayaṃ pajānāti, rūpanirodhaṃ pajānāti, rūpanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti.**“Reverend, it’s when an educated noble disciple understands form, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation.*";
P_HTM[4515]="*Vedanaṃ …**They understand feeling …*";
P_HTM[4516]="*saññaṃ …**perception …*";
P_HTM[4517]="*saṅkhāre …**choices …*";
P_HTM[4518]="*viññāṇaṃ pajānāti, viññāṇasamudayaṃ pajānāti, viññāṇanirodhaṃ pajānāti, viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti.**consciousness, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation.*";
P_HTM[4519]="*Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, vijjā;**This is called knowledge.*";
P_HTM[4520]="*ettāvatā ca vijjāgato hotī”ti.**And this is how a knowledgeable person is defined.”*";
