P_HTM[4526]="*koṭṭhike apare tayoti.* **";
P_HTM[4527]="*sn/sn22.136.xhtml==14. Kukkuḷavagga==14. Kukkuḷavaggo**Burning Chaff*";
P_HTM[4528]="*1. Kukkuḷasuttaṃ**Burning Chaff*";
P_HTM[4529]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4530]="*“Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, kukkuḷaṃ, vedanā kukkuḷā, saññā kukkuḷā, saṅkhārā kukkuḷā, viññāṇaṃ kukkuḷaṃ.**“Mendicants, form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are burning chaff.*";
P_HTM[4531]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmimpi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati, saññāyapi nibbindati, saṅkhāresupi nibbindati, viññāṇasmimpi nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness.*";
P_HTM[4532]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[4533]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[4534]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4535]="*2. Aniccasuttaṃ**Impermanence*";
P_HTM[4536]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4537]="*“Yaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ; tatra vo chando pahātabbo.**“Mendicants, you should give up desire for what is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[4538]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ?**And what is impermanent?*";
P_HTM[4539]="*Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ; tatra vo chando pahātabbo.**Form is impermanent; you should give up desire for it.*";
P_HTM[4540]="*Vedanā aniccā … pe …**Feeling …*";
P_HTM[4541]="*saññā …**Perception …*";
P_HTM[4542]="*saṅkhārā …**Choices …*";
P_HTM[4543]="*viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ; tatra vo chando pahātabbo.**Consciousness is impermanent; you should give up desire for it.*";
P_HTM[4544]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ; tatra vo chando pahātabbo”ti.**You should give up desire for what is impermanent.”*";
P_HTM[4545]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
