P_HTM[4666]="*sn/sn22.150.xhtml==15. Diṭṭhivagga==15. Diṭṭhivaggo**Views*";
P_HTM[4667]="*1. Ajjhattasuttaṃ**In Oneself*";
P_HTM[4668]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4669]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhan”ti?**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what, do pleasure and pain arise in oneself?”*";
P_HTM[4670]="*Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[4671]="*“rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati rūpaṃ upādāya uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.**“When form exists, because of grasping form, pleasure and pain arise in oneself.*";
P_HTM[4672]="*Vedanāya sati … pe …**When feeling …*";
P_HTM[4673]="*saññāya sati …**perception …*";
P_HTM[4674]="*saṅkhāresu sati …**choices …*";
P_HTM[4675]="*viññāṇe sati viññāṇaṃ upādāya uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ.**consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness, pleasure and pain arise in oneself.*";
P_HTM[4676]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4677]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[4678]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4679]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[4680]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4681]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya uppajjeyya ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhan”ti?**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would pleasure and pain arise in oneself?”*";
P_HTM[4682]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4683]="*“Vedanā … pe …**“Is feeling …*";
P_HTM[4684]="*saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[4685]="*saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[4686]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[4687]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4688]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[4689]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4690]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya uppajjeyya ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhan”ti?**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would pleasure and pain arise in oneself?”*";
P_HTM[4691]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4692]="*“Evaṃ passaṃ … pe …**“Seeing this …*";
P_HTM[4693]="*nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[4694]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4695]="*2. Etaṃmamasuttaṃ**This Is Mine*";
P_HTM[4696]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4697]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what,*";
P_HTM[4698]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassatī”ti?**does someone regard things like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[4699]="*Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[4700]="*“rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa … pe …**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form …*";
P_HTM[4701]="*viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa:**When consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness,*";
P_HTM[4702]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati.**someone regards it like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’*";
P_HTM[4703]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4704]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[4705]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[4706]="*vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attāti samanupasseyyāti?**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would you regard it like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[4707]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4708]="*“Vedanā …**“Is feeling …*";
P_HTM[4709]="*saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[4710]="*saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[4711]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[4712]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[4713]="*vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attāti samanupasseyyāti?**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would you regard it like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[4714]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4715]="*“Evaṃ passaṃ … pe …**“Seeing this …*";
P_HTM[4716]="*nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[4717]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4718]="*3. Soattāsuttaṃ**This Is My Self*";
P_HTM[4719]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4720]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[4721]="*‘so attā, so loko, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo’”ti?**‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After passing away I will be permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable’?”*";
P_HTM[4722]="*Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe ….**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[4723]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[4724]="*‘so attā, so loko, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo’ti.**‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After passing away I will be permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable.’*";
