P_HTM[4899]="*10. Ānandasuttaṃ**With Ānanda*";
P_HTM[4900]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4901]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā … pe … bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4902]="*“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti.**“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”*";
P_HTM[4903]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ānanda,**“What do you think, Ānanda?*";
P_HTM[4904]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[4905]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4906]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[4907]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4908]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[4909]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[4910]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
