P_HTM[5523]="*7. Hetusuttaṃ**Cause*";
P_HTM[5524]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5525]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5526]="*‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya.**‘There is no cause or condition for the corruption of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[5527]="*Ahetū appaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti.**Sentient beings are corrupted without cause or reason.*";
P_HTM[5528]="*Natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā.**There’s no cause or condition for the purification of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[5529]="*Ahetū appaccayā sattā visujjhanti.**Sentient beings are purified without cause or reason.*";
P_HTM[5530]="*Natthi balaṃ natthi vīriyaṃ natthi purisathāmo natthi purisaparakkamo.**There is no power, no energy, no manly strength or vigor.*";
P_HTM[5531]="*Sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā niyatisaṅgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’”ti?**All sentient beings, all living creatures, all beings, all souls lack control, power, and energy. Molded by destiny, circumstance, and nature, they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth’?”*";
P_HTM[5532]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[5533]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5534]="*‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo … pe …**‘There is no cause or condition …*";
P_HTM[5535]="*sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti.**they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth.’*";
