P_HTM[5566]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5567]="*8. Mahādiṭṭhisuttaṃ**The Extensive View*";
P_HTM[5568]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5569]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5570]="*‘sattime kāyā akaṭā, akaṭavidhā, animmitā, animmātā, vañjhā, kūṭaṭṭhā, esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā;**‘There are these seven substances that are not made, not derived, not created, without a creator, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a pillar.*";
P_HTM[5571]="*te na iñjanti, na vipariṇamanti, na aññamaññaṃ byābādhenti; nālaṃ aññamaññassa sukhāya vā dukkhāya vā sukhadukkhāya vā.**They don’t move or deteriorate or obstruct each other. They’re unable to cause pleasure, pain, or neutral feeling to each other.*";
P_HTM[5572]="*Katame satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[5573]="*Pathavīkāyo, āpokāyo, tejokāyo, vāyokāyo, sukhe, dukkhe, jīve sattame.**The substances of earth, water, fire, air; pleasure, pain, and the soul is the seventh.*";
P_HTM[5574]="*Ime satta kāyā akaṭā, akaṭavidhā, animmitā, animmātā, vañjhā, kūṭaṭṭhā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā;**These seven substances are not made, not derived, not created, without a creator, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a pillar.*";
P_HTM[5575]="*te na iñjanti, na vipariṇamanti, na aññamaññaṃ byābādhenti; nālaṃ aññamaññassa sukhāya vā dukkhāya vā sukhadukkhāya vā.**They don’t move or deteriorate or obstruct each other. They’re unable to cause pleasure, pain, or neutral feeling to each other.*";
P_HTM[5576]="*Yopi tiṇhena satthena sīsaṃ chindati, na sopi kañci jīvitā voropeti;**If you chop off someone’s head with a sharp sword, you don’t take anyone’s life.*";
P_HTM[5577]="*sattannaṃ tveva kāyānamantarena satthaṃ vivaramanupavisati.**The sword simply passes through the gap between the seven substances.*";
P_HTM[5578]="*Cuddasa kho panimāni yonipamukhasatasahassāni saṭṭhi ca satāni cha ca satāni pañca ca kammuno satāni pañca ca kammāni, tīṇi ca kammāni, kamme ca aḍḍhakamme ca dvaṭṭhipaṭipadā, dvaṭṭhantarakappā, chaḷābhijātiyo, aṭṭha purisabhūmiyo, ekūnapaññāsa ājīvakasate, ekūnapaññāsa paribbājakasate, ekūnapaññāsa nāgavāsasate, vīse indriyasate, tiṃse nirayasate, chattiṃsarajodhātuyo, satta saññīgabbhā, satta asaññīgabbhā, satta nigaṇṭhigabbhā, satta devā, satta mānusā, satta pesācā, satta sarā, satta pavuṭā, satta papātā, satta ca papātasatāni, satta supinā, satta supinasatāni, cullāsīti mahākappino satasahassāni, yāni bāle ca paṇḍite ca sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ karissanti.**There are 1.4 million main wombs, and 6,000, and 600. There are 500 deeds, and five, and three. There are deeds and half-deeds. There are 62 paths, 62 sub-eons, six classes of rebirth, and eight stages in a person’s life. There are 4,900 Ājīvaka ascetics, 4,900 wanderers, and 4,900 naked ascetics. There are 2,000 faculties, 3,000 hells, and 36 realms of dust. There are seven percipient embryos, seven non-percipient embryos, and seven embryos without attachments. There are seven gods, seven humans, and seven goblins. There are seven lakes, seven winds, seven cliffs, and 700 cliffs. There are seven dreams and 700 dreams. There are 8.4 million great eons through which the foolish and the astute transmigrate before making an end of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5579]="*Tattha natthi imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā aparipakkaṃ vā kammaṃ paripācessāmi;**And here there is no such thing as this: “By this precept or observance or mortification or spiritual life I shall force unripened deeds to bear their fruit, or eliminate old deeds by experiencing their results little by little”—for that cannot be.*";
P_HTM[5580]="*paripakkaṃ vā kammaṃ phussa phussa byantīkarissāmīti hevaṃ natthi doṇamite sukhadukkhe pariyantakate saṃsāre, natthi hāyanavaḍḍhane, natthi ukkaṃsāvakaṃse.**Pleasure and pain are allotted. Transmigration lasts only for a limited period, so there’s no increase or decrease, no getting better or worse.*";
P_HTM[5581]="*Seyyathāpi nāma suttaguḷe khitte nibbeṭhiyamānameva paleti;**It’s like how, when you toss a ball of string, it rolls away unraveling.*";
P_HTM[5582]="*evameva bāle ca paṇḍite ca nibbeṭhiyamānā sukhadukkhaṃ palentī’”ti?**In the same way, after transmigrating the foolish and the astute will make an end of suffering’?”*";
P_HTM[5583]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[5584]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5585]="*‘sattime kāyā akaṭā, akaṭavidhā … pe …**‘There are these seven substances that are not made …*";
P_HTM[5586]="*sukhadukkhaṃ palentī’ti.**the foolish and the astute will make an end of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[5587]="*Vedanāya sati … pe …**When feeling …*";
P_HTM[5588]="*saññāya sati …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5589]="*saṅkhāresu sati …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5590]="*viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5591]="*‘sattime kāyā akaṭā, akaṭavidhā … pe …**‘There are these seven substances that are not made …*";
P_HTM[5592]="*sukhadukkhaṃ palentī’ti.**the foolish and the astute will make an end of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[5593]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5594]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5595]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5596]="*“yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5597]="*‘sattime kāyā akaṭā akaṭavidhā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5598]="*sukhadukkhaṃ palentī’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5599]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5600]="*“Yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**“That which is seen, heard, thought, known, sought, and explored by the mind: is that permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5601]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante … pe …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5602]="*api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would such a view arise?”*";
P_HTM[5603]="*‘sattime kāyā akaṭā akaṭavidhā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5604]="*nibbeṭhiyamānā sukhadukkhaṃ palentī’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5605]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5606]="*“Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa imesu ca ṭhānesu kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāyapissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti—**“When a noble disciple has given up doubt in these six cases, and has given up doubt in suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation,*";
P_HTM[5607]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.**they’re called a noble disciple who is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[5608]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5609]="*9. Sassatadiṭṭhisuttaṃ**The World is Eternal*";
P_HTM[5610]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5611]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5612]="*‘sassato loko’”ti?**‘The world is eternal’?”*";
P_HTM[5613]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[5614]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5615]="*‘sassato loko’ti.**‘The world is eternal.’*";
P_HTM[5616]="*Vedanāya sati … pe …**When feeling … perception …*";
P_HTM[5617]="*saṅkhāresu sati …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5618]="*viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5619]="*‘sassato loko’ti.**‘The world is eternal.’*";
P_HTM[5620]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5621]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5622]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5623]="*vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5624]="*‘sassato loko’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5625]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5626]="*“Vedanā …* **";
P_HTM[5627]="*saññā …* **";
P_HTM[5628]="*saṅkhārā …* **";
P_HTM[5629]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5630]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5631]="*api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5632]="*‘sassato loko’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5633]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5634]="*“Yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5635]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5636]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5637]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5638]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would such a view arise?”*";
P_HTM[5639]="*‘sassato loko’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5640]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5641]="*“Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa imesu ca ṭhānesu kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāyapissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti—**“When a noble disciple has given up doubt in these six cases, and has given up doubt in suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation,*";
P_HTM[5642]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.**they’re called a noble disciple who is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[5643]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5644]="*10. Asassatadiṭṭhisuttaṃ**The World Is Not Eternal*";
P_HTM[5645]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5646]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5647]="*‘asassato loko’”ti?**‘The world is not eternal’?”*";
P_HTM[5648]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[5649]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati … pe …**“When form exists …” …*";
P_HTM[5650]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5651]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5652]="*api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5653]="*‘asassato loko’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5654]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5655]="*“Yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5656]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5657]="*api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would such a view arise?”*";
P_HTM[5658]="*‘asassato loko’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5659]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5660]="*“Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa imesu ca ṭhānesu kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāyapissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti—**“When a noble disciple has given up doubt in these six cases, and has given up doubt in suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation,*";
P_HTM[5661]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.**they’re called a noble disciple who is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[5662]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5663]="*11. Antavāsuttaṃ**The World Is Finite*";
P_HTM[5664]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5665]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5666]="*‘antavā loko’”ti?**‘The world is finite’?” …*";
P_HTM[5667]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5668]="*niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5669]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5670]="*12. Anantavāsuttaṃ**The World Is Infinite*";
P_HTM[5671]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5672]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5673]="*‘anantavā loko’”ti?**‘The world is infinite’?” …*";
P_HTM[5674]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5675]="*niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5676]="*Dvādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5677]="*13. Taṃjīvaṃtaṃsarīraṃsuttaṃ**The Soul and the Body Are Identical*";
P_HTM[5678]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5679]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5680]="*‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’”ti?**‘The soul and the body are identical’?” …*";
P_HTM[5681]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5682]="*niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5683]="*Terasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5684]="*14. Aññaṃjīvaṃaññaṃsarīraṃsuttaṃ**The Soul and the Body Are Different Things*";
P_HTM[5685]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5686]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5687]="*‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’”ti?**‘The soul and the body are different things’?” …*";
P_HTM[5688]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5689]="*niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5690]="*Cuddasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5691]="*15. Hotitathāgatosuttaṃ**A Realized One Exists*";
P_HTM[5692]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5693]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5694]="*‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘A Realized One exists after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5695]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5696]="*niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5697]="*Pannarasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5698]="*16. Nahotitathāgatosuttaṃ**A Realized One Doesn’t Exist*";
P_HTM[5699]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5700]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5701]="*‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘A Realized One doesn’t exist after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5702]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5703]="*niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5704]="*Soḷasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5705]="*17. Hoticanacahotitathāgatosuttaṃ**A Realized One Both Exists and Doesn’t Exist*";
P_HTM[5706]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5707]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5708]="*‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5709]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5710]="*niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5711]="*Sattarasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5712]="*18. Nevahotinanahotitathāgatosuttaṃ**A Realized One Neither Exists Nor Doesn’t Exist*";
P_HTM[5713]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5714]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5715]="*‘neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’?”*";
P_HTM[5716]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[5717]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5718]="*‘neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti … pe ….**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’ …*";
P_HTM[5719]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5720]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5721]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5722]="*vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5723]="*‘neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’?”*";
P_HTM[5724]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5725]="*“Yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**“That which is seen, heard, thought, known, sought, and explored by the mind: is that permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5726]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5727]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[5728]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5729]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5730]="*‘neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’?”*";
P_HTM[5731]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5732]="*“Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa imesu ca ṭhānesu kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhasamudayepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhanirodhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāyapissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti—**“When a noble disciple has given up doubt in these six cases, and has given up doubt in suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation,*";
P_HTM[5733]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti.**they’re called a noble disciple who is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[5734]="*Aṭṭhārasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5735]="*Sotāpattivaggo.* **";
P_HTM[5736]="*Aṭṭhārasaveyyākaraṇaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5737]="*Vātaṃ etaṃ mama,* **";
P_HTM[5738]="*so attā no ca me siyā;* **";
P_HTM[5739]="*Natthi karoto hetu ca,* **";
P_HTM[5740]="*mahādiṭṭhena aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5741]="*Sassato loko ca,* **";
P_HTM[5742]="*Asassato ca antavā ca;* **";
P_HTM[5743]="*Anantavā ca taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīranti,* **";
P_HTM[5744]="*Aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīranti ca.* **";
P_HTM[5745]="*Hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti,* **";
P_HTM[5746]="*Na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti;* **";
P_HTM[5747]="*Neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti.* **";
P_HTM[5748]="*sn/sn24.19.xhtml==2. Dutiyagamanavagga==2. Dutiyagamanavaggo**The Second Round*";
P_HTM[5749]="*1. Vātasuttaṃ**Winds*";
P_HTM[5750]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5751]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5752]="*‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā, esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti?**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar’?”*";
P_HTM[5753]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[5754]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5755]="*‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’ti.**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’*";
P_HTM[5756]="*Vedanāya sati … pe …**When feeling …*";
P_HTM[5757]="*saññāya sati … pe …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5758]="*saṅkhāresu sati …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5759]="*viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5760]="*‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’ti.**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’*";
P_HTM[5761]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5762]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5763]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … vipariṇāmadhammaṃ,**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5764]="*api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya—**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5765]="*na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā”ti?**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar’?”*";
P_HTM[5766]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5767]="*“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe sati, dukkhaṃ upādāya, dukkhaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“And so, when suffering exists, because of grasping suffering and insisting on suffering, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5768]="*‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti.**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’*";
P_HTM[5769]="*“Vedanā …**Is feeling …*";
P_HTM[5770]="*saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5771]="*saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5772]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5773]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … vipariṇāmadhammaṃ,**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5774]="*api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would such a view arise?”*";
P_HTM[5775]="*‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5776]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5777]="*“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe sati, dukkhaṃ upādāya, dukkhaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:**“And so, when suffering exists, because of grasping suffering and insisting on suffering, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5778]="*‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā, esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti.**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’”*";
P_HTM[5779]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5780]="*18. Nevahotinanahotisuttaṃ**20–35. Etaṃmamādisutta*";
P_HTM[5781]="*(Purimavagge viya aṭṭhārasa veyyākaraṇāni vitthāretabbānīti.)**(These should be expanded in the same way as discourses 2 through 17 of the previous chapter.)*";
P_HTM[5782]="*Sattarasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5783]="*19. Rūpīattāsuttaṃ**Neither Exists Nor Doesn’t Exist*";
P_HTM[5784]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5785]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5786]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’?”*";
P_HTM[5787]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[5788]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5789]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti.**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death.’*";
P_HTM[5790]="*“Vedanāya sati …**When feeling …*";
P_HTM[5791]="*saññāya sati …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5792]="*saṅkhāresu sati …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5793]="*viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5794]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti.**‘a Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death.’*";
P_HTM[5795]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5796]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5797]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … vipariṇāmadhammaṃ,**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5798]="*api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5799]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5800]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5801]="*“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe sati, dukkhaṃ upādāya, dukkhaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“And so, when suffering exists, because of grasping suffering and insisting on suffering, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5802]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti.**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death.’” …*";
P_HTM[5803]="*“Vedanā …**“Is feeling …*";
P_HTM[5804]="*saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5805]="*saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5806]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5807]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … vipariṇāmadhammaṃ,**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5808]="*api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would such a view arise?”*";
P_HTM[5809]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5810]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5811]="*“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe sati, dukkhaṃ upādāya dukkhaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“And so, when suffering exists, because of grasping suffering and insisting on suffering, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5812]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti.**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death.’”*";
P_HTM[5813]="*Aṭṭhārasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5814]="*20. Arūpīattāsuttaṃ**The Self Has Form*";
P_HTM[5815]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5816]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5817]="*‘rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘The self has form and is sound after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5818]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5819]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:* **";
P_HTM[5820]="*‘rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5821]="*Vedanāya sati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5822]="*saññāya sati …* **";
P_HTM[5823]="*saṅkhāresu sati …* **";
P_HTM[5824]="*viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:* **";
P_HTM[5825]="*‘rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5826]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5827]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5828]="*vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5829]="*‘rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5830]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5831]="*“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe sati, dukkhaṃ upādāya, dukkhaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:* **";
P_HTM[5832]="*‘rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5833]="*“Vedanā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5834]="*“no hetaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5835]="*“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe sati, dukkhaṃ upādāya, dukkhaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:* **";
P_HTM[5836]="*‘rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5837]="*Ekūnavīsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5838]="*21. Rūpīcaarūpīcaattāsuttaṃ**The Self Is Formless*";
P_HTM[5839]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5840]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5841]="*‘arūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘The self is formless and is sound after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5842]="*(Peyyālo.)* **";
P_HTM[5843]="*Vīsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5844]="*22. Nevarūpīnārūpīattāsuttaṃ**The Self Has Form and Is Formless*";
P_HTM[5845]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5846]="*“Rūpī ca arūpī ca attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā”ti … pe ….**“‘The self has form and is formless, and is sound after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5847]="*Ekavīsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5848]="*23. Ekantasukhīsuttaṃ**The Self Neither Has Form Nor Is Formless*";
P_HTM[5849]="*“Neva rūpī nārūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā”ti … pe ….**“‘The self neither has form nor is formless, and is sound after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5850]="*Bāvīsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5851]="*24. Ekantadukkhīsuttaṃ**The Self Is Perfectly Happy*";
P_HTM[5852]="*“Ekantasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā”ti … pe ….**“‘The self is perfectly happy, and is sound after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5853]="*Tevīsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5854]="*25. Sukhadukkhīsuttaṃ**Exclusively Suffering*";
P_HTM[5855]="*“Ekantadukkhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā”ti … pe ….**“‘The self is exclusively suffering, and is sound after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5856]="*Catuvīsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5857]="*26. Adukkhamasukhīsuttaṃ**The Self Is Happy and Suffering*";
P_HTM[5858]="*“Sukhadukkhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā”ti … pe ….**“‘The self is happy and suffering, and is sound after death’?” …*";
P_HTM[5859]="*Pañcavīsatimaṃ.* **";
