P_HTM[5908]="*26. Adukkhamasukhīsuttaṃ**Winds*";
P_HTM[5909]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5910]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5911]="*‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti?**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar’?”*";
P_HTM[5912]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe ….**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[5913]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati—**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5914]="*na vātā vāyanti … pe …**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’*";
P_HTM[5915]="*vedanāya sati …**When feeling …*";
P_HTM[5916]="*saññāya sati …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5917]="*saṅkhāresu sati …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5918]="*viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5919]="*‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’ti.**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’*";
P_HTM[5920]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5921]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5922]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5923]="*vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would the view arise:*";
P_HTM[5924]="*‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti?**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar’.”*";
P_HTM[5925]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5926]="*“Iti kho, bhikkhave, yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ.**“And so, what’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[5927]="*Tasmiṃ sati, tadupādāya, evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**When this exists, grasping at this, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5928]="*‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti.**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’*";
P_HTM[5929]="*“Vedanā …**Is feeling …*";
P_HTM[5930]="*saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5931]="*saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5932]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5933]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … vipariṇāmadhammaṃ,**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5934]="*api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya:* **";
P_HTM[5935]="*‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5936]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[5937]="*“Iti kho, bhikkhave, yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ.**“And so, what’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[5938]="*Tasmiṃ sati, tadupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**When this exists, grasping at this, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[5939]="*‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti.**‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’”*";
