P_HTM[6021]="*3. Viññāṇasuttaṃ**The Self Is Neither Happy Nor Suffering*";
P_HTM[6022]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6023]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise:*";
P_HTM[6024]="*‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?**‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and is sound after death’?”*";
P_HTM[6025]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe ….**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[6026]="*“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:**“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises:*";
P_HTM[6027]="*‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’ti.**‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and is sound after death.’*";
