P_HTM[6040]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6041]="*“Vedanā …**“Is feeling …*";
P_HTM[6042]="*saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[6043]="*saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[6044]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[6045]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6046]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[6047]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6048]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[6049]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[6050]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6051]="*“Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**“So you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[6052]="*Yā kāci vedanā …**You should truly see any kind of feeling …*";
P_HTM[6053]="*yā kāci saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[6054]="*ye keci saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[6055]="*yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā, oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[6056]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmimpi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati, saññāyapi nibbindati, saṅkhāresupi nibbindati, viññāṇasmimpi nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness.*";
P_HTM[6057]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[6058]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[6059]="*Catutthapeyyālo.* **";
P_HTM[6060]="*Purimagamane aṭṭhārasa veyyākaraṇā,* **";
P_HTM[6061]="*Dutiyagamane chabbīsaṃ vitthāretabbāni;* **";
P_HTM[6062]="*Tatiyagamane chabbīsaṃ vitthāretabbāni,* **";
P_HTM[6063]="*Catutthagamane chabbīsaṃ vitthāretabbāni.* **";
P_HTM[6064]="*Diṭṭhisaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on views are complete.*";
P_HTM[6065]="*25. Okkantasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6066]="*4. Samphassasuttaṃ**The Eye*";
P_HTM[6067]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6068]="*“Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi;**“Mendicants, the eye is impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6069]="*sotaṃ aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi;**The ear,*";
P_HTM[6070]="*ghānaṃ aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi;**nose,*";
P_HTM[6071]="*jivhā aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī;**tongue,*";
P_HTM[6072]="*kāyo anicco vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi;**body,*";
P_HTM[6073]="*mano anicco vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī.**and mind are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6074]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ saddahati adhimuccati—ayaṃ vuccati saddhānusārī, okkanto sammattaniyāmaṃ, sappurisabhūmiṃ okkanto, vītivatto puthujjanabhūmiṃ;**Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. They’ve arrived at inevitability regarding the right path, they’ve arrived at the level of the good person, and they’ve transcended the level of the bad person.*";
P_HTM[6075]="*abhabbo taṃ kammaṃ kātuṃ, yaṃ kammaṃ katvā nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjeyya;**They can’t do any deed which would make them be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[6076]="*abhabbo ca tāva kālaṃ kātuṃ yāva na sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchikaroti.**They can’t die without realizing the fruit of stream-entry.*";
P_HTM[6077]="*Yassa kho, bhikkhave, ime dhammā evaṃ paññāya mattaso nijjhānaṃ khamanti, ayaṃ vuccati: ‘dhammānusārī, okkanto sammattaniyāmaṃ, sappurisabhūmiṃ okkanto, vītivatto puthujjanabhūmiṃ;**Someone who accepts these principles after considering them with a degree of wisdom is called a follower of the teachings. They’ve arrived at inevitability regarding the right path, they’ve arrived at the level of the good person, and they’ve transcended the level of the bad person.*";
P_HTM[6078]="*abhabbo taṃ kammaṃ kātuṃ, yaṃ kammaṃ katvā nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjeyya;**They can’t do any deed which would make them be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[6079]="*abhabbo ca tāva kālaṃ kātuṃ yāva na sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchikaroti’.**They can’t die without realizing the fruit of stream-entry.*";
P_HTM[6080]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ pajānāti evaṃ passati, ayaṃ vuccati: ‘sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano’”ti.**Someone who understands and sees these principles is called a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[6081]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6082]="*5. Samphassajāsuttaṃ**Sights*";
P_HTM[6083]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6084]="*“Rūpā, bhikkhave, aniccā vipariṇāmino aññathābhāvino;**“Mendicants, sights are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6085]="*saddā aniccā vipariṇāmino aññathābhāvino;**Sounds,*";
P_HTM[6086]="*gandhā aniccā vipariṇāmino aññathābhāvino;**smells,*";
P_HTM[6087]="*rasā aniccā vipariṇāmino aññathābhāvino;**tastes,*";
P_HTM[6088]="*phoṭṭhabbā aniccā vipariṇāmino aññathābhāvino;**touches,*";
P_HTM[6089]="*dhammā aniccā vipariṇāmino aññathābhāvino.**and thoughts are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6090]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ saddahati adhimuccati, ayaṃ vuccati saddhānusārī, okkanto sammattaniyāmaṃ, sappurisabhūmiṃ okkanto, vītivatto puthujjanabhūmiṃ;**Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. They’ve arrived at inevitability regarding the right path, they’ve arrived at the level of the good person, and they’ve transcended the level of the bad person.*";
P_HTM[6091]="*abhabbo taṃ kammaṃ kātuṃ, yaṃ kammaṃ katvā nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjeyya;**They can’t do any deed which would make them be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[6092]="*abhabbo ca tāva kālaṃ kātuṃ yāva na sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchikaroti.**They can’t die without realizing the fruit of stream-entry.*";
P_HTM[6093]="*Yassa kho, bhikkhave, ime dhammā evaṃ paññāya mattaso nijjhānaṃ khamanti, ayaṃ vuccati: ‘dhammānusārī, okkanto sammattaniyāmaṃ, sappurisabhūmiṃ okkanto, vītivatto puthujjanabhūmiṃ;**Someone who accepts these principles after considering them with a degree of wisdom is called a follower of the teachings. They’ve arrived at inevitability regarding the right path, they’ve arrived at the level of the good person, and they’ve transcended the level of the bad person.*";
P_HTM[6094]="*abhabbo taṃ kammaṃ kātuṃ, yaṃ kammaṃ katvā nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjeyya;**They can’t do any deed which would make them be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[6095]="*abhabbo ca tāva kālaṃ kātuṃ yāva na sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchikaroti’.**They can’t die without realizing the fruit of stream-entry.*";
P_HTM[6096]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ pajānāti evaṃ passati, ayaṃ vuccati:**Someone who understands and sees these principles is called*";
P_HTM[6097]="*‘sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano’”ti.**a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[6098]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6099]="*6. Rūpasaññāsuttaṃ**Consciousness*";
P_HTM[6100]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6101]="*“Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi;**“Mendicants, eye consciousness is impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6102]="*sotaviññāṇaṃ …**Ear consciousness,*";
P_HTM[6103]="*ghānaviññāṇaṃ …**nose consciousness,*";
P_HTM[6104]="*jivhāviññāṇaṃ …**tongue consciousness,*";
P_HTM[6105]="*kāyaviññāṇaṃ …**body consciousness,*";
P_HTM[6106]="*manoviññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi.**and mind consciousness are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6107]="*Yo bhikkhave … pe …**Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. …”*";
P_HTM[6108]="*sambodhiparāyano”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6109]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6110]="*7. Rūpasañcetanāsuttaṃ**Contact*";
P_HTM[6111]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6112]="*“Cakkhusamphasso, bhikkhave, anicco vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī;**“Mendicants, eye contact is impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6113]="*sotasamphasso …**Ear contact,*";
P_HTM[6114]="*ghānasamphasso …**nose contact,*";
P_HTM[6115]="*jivhāsamphasso …**tongue contact,*";
P_HTM[6116]="*kāyasamphasso …**body contact,*";
P_HTM[6117]="*manosamphasso anicco vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī.**and mind contact are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6118]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ saddahati adhimuccati, ayaṃ vuccati ‘saddhānusārī … pe …**Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. …”*";
P_HTM[6119]="*sambodhiparāyano’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6120]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6121]="*8. Rūpataṇhāsuttaṃ**Feeling*";
P_HTM[6122]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6123]="*“Cakkhusamphassajā, bhikkhave, vedanā aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī;**“Mendicants, feeling born of eye contact is impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6124]="*sotasamphassajā vedanā … pe …**Feeling born of ear contact,*";
P_HTM[6125]="*ghānasamphassajā vedanā … pe …**feeling born of nose contact,*";
P_HTM[6126]="*jivhāsamphassajā vedanā … pe …**feeling born of tongue contact,*";
P_HTM[6127]="*kāyasamphassajā vedanā … pe …**feeling born of body contact,*";
P_HTM[6128]="*manosamphassajā vedanā aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī.**and feeling born of mind contact are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6129]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ saddahati adhimuccati, ayaṃ vuccati ‘saddhānusārī … pe …**Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. …”*";
P_HTM[6130]="*sambodhiparāyano’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6131]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6132]="*9. Pathavīdhātusuttaṃ**Perception*";
P_HTM[6133]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6134]="*“Rūpasaññā, bhikkhave, aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī;**“Mendicants, perception of sights is impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6135]="*saddasaññā …**Perception of sounds,*";
P_HTM[6136]="*gandhasaññā …**perception of smells,*";
P_HTM[6137]="*rasasaññā …**perception of tastes,*";
P_HTM[6138]="*phoṭṭhabbasaññā …**perception of touches,*";
P_HTM[6139]="*dhammasaññā aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī.**and perception of thoughts are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6140]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ saddahati adhimuccati, ayaṃ vuccati ‘saddhānusārī … pe …**Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. …”*";
P_HTM[6141]="*sambodhiparāyano’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6142]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
