P_HTM[6154]="*1. Cakkhusuttaṃ**Craving For Sights*";
P_HTM[6155]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6156]="*“Rūpataṇhā, bhikkhave, aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī;**“Mendicants, craving for sights is impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6157]="*saddataṇhā …**Craving for sounds,*";
P_HTM[6158]="*gandhataṇhā …**craving for smells,*";
P_HTM[6159]="*rasataṇhā …**craving for tastes,*";
P_HTM[6160]="*phoṭṭhabbataṇhā …**craving for touches,*";
P_HTM[6161]="*dhammataṇhā aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī.**and craving for thoughts are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6162]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ saddahati adhimuccati, ayaṃ vuccati ‘saddhānusārī … pe …**Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. …”*";
P_HTM[6163]="*sambodhiparāyano’”ti.* **";
