P_HTM[6165]="*2. Rūpasuttaṃ**Elements*";
P_HTM[6166]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6167]="*“Pathavīdhātu, bhikkhave, aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī;**“Mendicants, the earth element is impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6168]="*āpodhātu …**The water element,*";
P_HTM[6169]="*tejodhātu …**the fire element,*";
P_HTM[6170]="*vāyodhātu …**the air element,*";
P_HTM[6171]="*ākāsadhātu …**the space element,*";
P_HTM[6172]="*viññāṇadhātu aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī.**and the consciousness element are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6173]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ saddahati adhimuccati, ayaṃ vuccati ‘saddhānusārī … pe …**Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. …”*";
P_HTM[6174]="*sambodhiparāyano’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6175]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6176]="*3. Viññāṇasuttaṃ**The Aggregates*";
P_HTM[6177]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6178]="*“Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi;**“Mendicants, form is impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6179]="*vedanā aniccā vipariṇāmī aññathābhāvī;**Feeling,*";
P_HTM[6180]="*saññā …**perception,*";
P_HTM[6181]="*saṅkhārā aniccā vipariṇāmino aññathābhāvino;**choices,*";
P_HTM[6182]="*viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ vipariṇāmi aññathābhāvi.**and consciousness are impermanent, perishing, and changing.*";
P_HTM[6183]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ saddahati adhimuccati, ayaṃ vuccati saddhānusārī, okkanto sammattaniyāmaṃ, sappurisabhūmiṃ okkanto, vītivatto puthujjanabhūmiṃ;**Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. They’ve arrived at inevitability regarding the right path, they’ve arrived at the level of the good person, and they’ve transcended the level of the bad person.*";
P_HTM[6184]="*abhabbo taṃ kammaṃ kātuṃ, yaṃ kammaṃ katvā nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjeyya;**They can’t do any deed which would make them be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[6185]="*abhabbo ca tāva kālaṃ kātuṃ yāva na sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchikaroti.**They can’t die without realizing the fruit of stream-entry.*";
P_HTM[6186]="*Yassa kho, bhikkhave, ime dhammā evaṃ paññāya mattaso nijjhānaṃ khamanti, ayaṃ vuccati: ‘dhammānusārī, okkanto sammattaniyāmaṃ, sappurisabhūmiṃ okkanto, vītivatto puthujjanabhūmiṃ;**Someone who accepts these principles after considering them with a degree of wisdom is called a follower of the teachings. They’ve arrived at inevitability regarding the right path, they’ve arrived at the level of the good person, and they’ve transcended the level of the bad person.*";
P_HTM[6187]="*abhabbo taṃ kammaṃ kātuṃ, yaṃ kammaṃ katvā nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā pettivisayaṃ vā upapajjeyya;**They can’t do any deed which would make them be reborn in hell, the animal realm, or the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[6188]="*abhabbo ca tāva kālaṃ kātuṃ yāva na sotāpattiphalaṃ sacchikaroti’.**They can’t die without realizing the fruit of stream-entry.*";
P_HTM[6189]="*Yo, bhikkhave, ime dhamme evaṃ pajānāti evaṃ passati, ayaṃ vuccati:**Someone who understands and sees these principles is called*";
P_HTM[6190]="*‘sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano’”ti.**a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”*";
P_HTM[6191]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6192]="*Cakkhuvaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6193]="*Cakkhu rūpañca viññāṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6194]="*phasso ca vedanāya ca;* **";
P_HTM[6195]="*Saññā ca cetanā taṇhā,* **";
P_HTM[6196]="*dhātu khandhena te dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[6197]="*Okkantasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on arrival are complete.*";
P_HTM[6198]="*26. Uppādasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6199]="*4. Samphassasuttaṃ**The Eye*";
P_HTM[6200]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6201]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, cakkhussa uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**“Mendicants, the arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of the eye is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6202]="*Yo sotassa uppādo ṭhiti … pe …**The arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of the ear,*";
P_HTM[6203]="*yo ghānassa uppādo ṭhiti …**nose,*";
P_HTM[6204]="*yo jivhāya uppādo ṭhiti …**tongue,*";
P_HTM[6205]="*yo kāyassa uppādo ṭhiti …**body,*";
P_HTM[6206]="*yo manassa uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**and mind is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6207]="*Yo ca, bhikkhave, cakkhussa nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo.**The cessation, settling, and ending of the eye is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6208]="*Yo sotassa nirodho … pe …**The cessation, settling, and ending of the ear,*";
P_HTM[6209]="*yo ghānassa nirodho …**nose,*";
P_HTM[6210]="*yo kāyassa nirodho …**body,*";
P_HTM[6211]="*yo manassa nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**and mind is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6212]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6213]="*5. Samphassajasuttaṃ**Sights*";
P_HTM[6214]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6215]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**“Mendicants, the arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of sights is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6216]="*Yo saddānaṃ …**The arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of sounds,*";
P_HTM[6217]="*yo gandhānaṃ …**smells,*";
P_HTM[6218]="*yo rasānaṃ …**tastes,*";
P_HTM[6219]="*yo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …**touches,*";
P_HTM[6220]="*yo dhammānaṃ uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**and thoughts is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6221]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo.**The cessation, settling, and ending of sights,*";
P_HTM[6222]="*Yo saddānaṃ …**sounds,*";
P_HTM[6223]="*yo gandhānaṃ …**smells,*";
P_HTM[6224]="*yo rasānaṃ …**tastes,*";
P_HTM[6225]="*yo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …**touches,*";
P_HTM[6226]="*yo dhammānaṃ nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**and thoughts is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6227]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6228]="*6. Saññāsuttaṃ**Consciousness*";
P_HTM[6229]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6230]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññāṇassa uppādo ṭhiti … pe …**“Mendicants, the arising of eye consciousness …*";
P_HTM[6231]="*jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6232]="*yo manoviññāṇassa uppādo ṭhiti … pe …**mind consciousness …*";
P_HTM[6233]="*jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**is the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6234]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññāṇassa nirodho … pe …**The cessation of eye consciousness …*";
P_HTM[6235]="*jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6236]="*yo manoviññāṇassa nirodho … pe …**mind consciousness …*";
P_HTM[6237]="*jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**is the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6238]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6239]="*7. Sañcetanāsuttaṃ**Contact*";
P_HTM[6240]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6241]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, cakkhusamphassassa uppādo ṭhiti … pe …**“Mendicants, the arising of eye contact …*";
P_HTM[6242]="*jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6243]="*yo manosamphassassa uppādo ṭhiti … pe …**mind contact …*";
P_HTM[6244]="*jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**is the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6245]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, cakkhusamphassassa nirodho … pe …**The cessation of eye contact …*";
P_HTM[6246]="*jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6247]="*yo manosamphassassa nirodho … pe …**mind contact …*";
P_HTM[6248]="*jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**is the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6249]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6250]="*8. Taṇhāsuttaṃ**Feeling*";
P_HTM[6251]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6252]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, cakkhusamphassajāya vedanāya uppādo ṭhiti … pe … jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo … pe ….**“Mendicants, the arising of feeling born of eye contact …*";
P_HTM[6253]="*Yo manosamphassajāya vedanāya uppādo ṭhiti … pe …**the arising of feeling born of mind contact …*";
P_HTM[6254]="*jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**is the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6255]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, cakkhusamphassajāya vedanāya nirodho vūpasamo … pe …**The cessation of feeling born of eye contact …*";
P_HTM[6256]="*jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6257]="*yo manosamphassajāya vedanāya nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**the cessation of feeling born of mind contact … is the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6258]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6259]="*9. Dhātusuttaṃ**Perception*";
P_HTM[6260]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6261]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, rūpasaññāya uppādo ṭhiti … pe …**“Mendicants, the arising of perception of sights …*";
P_HTM[6262]="*jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6263]="*yo dhammasaññāya uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**perception of thoughts … is the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6264]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, rūpasaññāya nirodho … pe …**The cessation of perception of sights …*";
P_HTM[6265]="*jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6266]="*yo dhammasaññāya nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**perception of thoughts … is the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6267]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6268]="*10. Khandhasuttaṃ**Intention*";
P_HTM[6269]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6270]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, rūpasañcetanāya uppādo ṭhiti … pe …**“Mendicants, the arising of intentions regarding sights …*";
P_HTM[6271]="*jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6272]="*yo dhammasañcetanāya uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**intentions regarding thoughts … is the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6273]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, rūpasañcetanāya nirodho … pe …**The cessation of intentions regarding sights …*";
P_HTM[6274]="*jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6275]="*yo dhammasañcetanāya nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**intentions regarding thoughts … is the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6276]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6277]="*1. Cakkhusuttaṃ**Craving*";
P_HTM[6278]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6279]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, rūpataṇhāya uppādo ṭhiti … pe …**“Mendicants, the arising of craving for sights …*";
P_HTM[6280]="*jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6281]="*yo dhammataṇhāya uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**craving for thoughts … is the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6282]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, rūpataṇhāya nirodho … pe …**The cessation of craving for sights …*";
P_HTM[6283]="*jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6284]="*yo dhammataṇhāya nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**craving for thoughts … is the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6285]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6286]="*2. Rūpasuttaṃ**Elements*";
P_HTM[6287]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6288]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo … pe … jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo;**“Mendicants, the arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of the earth element,*";
P_HTM[6289]="*yo āpodhātuyā …**the water element,*";
P_HTM[6290]="*yo tejodhātuyā …**the fire element,*";
P_HTM[6291]="*yo vāyodhātuyā …**the air element,*";
P_HTM[6292]="*yo ākāsadhātuyā …**the space element,*";
P_HTM[6293]="*yo viññāṇadhātuyā uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**and the consciousness element is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6294]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā nirodho … pe … jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo;**The cessation of the earth element,*";
P_HTM[6295]="*yo āpodhātuyā nirodho …**the water element,*";
P_HTM[6296]="*yo tejodhātuyā nirodho …**the fire element,*";
P_HTM[6297]="*yo vāyodhātuyā nirodho …**the air element,*";
P_HTM[6298]="*yo ākāsadhātuyā nirodho …**the space element,*";
P_HTM[6299]="*yo viññāṇadhātuyā nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**and the consciousness element is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6300]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6301]="*3. Viññāṇasuttaṃ**The Aggregates*";
P_HTM[6302]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6303]="*“Yo kho, bhikkhave, rūpassa uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**“Mendicants, the arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of form is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6304]="*Yo vedanāya …**The arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of feeling,*";
P_HTM[6305]="*yo saññāya …**perception,*";
P_HTM[6306]="*yo saṅkhārānaṃ …**choices,*";
P_HTM[6307]="*yo viññāṇassa uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**and consciousness is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6308]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, rūpassa nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo.**The cessation, settling, and ending of form is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[6309]="*Yo vedanāya …**The cessation, settling, and ending of feeling,*";
P_HTM[6310]="*yo saññāya …**perception,*";
P_HTM[6311]="*yo saṅkhārānaṃ …**choices,*";
P_HTM[6312]="*yo viññāṇassa nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**and consciousness is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[6313]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6314]="*Uppādavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6315]="*Cakkhu rūpañca viññāṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6316]="*phasso ca vedanāya ca;* **";
P_HTM[6317]="*Saññā ca cetanā taṇhā,* **";
P_HTM[6318]="*dhātu khandhena te dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[6319]="*Uppādasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on arising are complete.*";
P_HTM[6320]="*27. Kilesasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6321]="*4. Samphassasuttaṃ**The Eye*";
P_HTM[6322]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6323]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, cakkhusmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for the eye,*";
P_HTM[6324]="*Yo sotasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**ear,*";
P_HTM[6325]="*Yo ghānasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**nose,*";
P_HTM[6326]="*Yo jivhāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**tongue,*";
P_HTM[6327]="*Yo kāyasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**body,*";
P_HTM[6328]="*Yo manasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**or mind is a corruption of the mind.*";
P_HTM[6329]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno imesu chasu ṭhānesu cetaso upakkileso pahīno hoti, nekkhammaninnañcassa cittaṃ hoti.**When a mendicant has given up mental corruption in these six cases, their mind inclines to renunciation.*";
P_HTM[6330]="*Nekkhammaparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ kammaniyaṃ khāyati, abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.**A mind imbued with renunciation is declared to be capable of directly knowing anything that can be realized.”*";
P_HTM[6331]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6332]="*5. Samphassajasuttaṃ**Sights*";
P_HTM[6333]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6334]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, rūpesu chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for sights,*";
P_HTM[6335]="*Yo saddesu …**sounds,*";
P_HTM[6336]="*yo gandhesu …**smells,*";
P_HTM[6337]="*yo rasesu …**tastes,*";
P_HTM[6338]="*yo phoṭṭhabbesu …**touches,*";
P_HTM[6339]="*yo dhammesu chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**or thoughts is a corruption of the mind.*";
P_HTM[6340]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno imesu chasu ṭhānesu cetaso upakkileso pahīno hoti, nekkhammaninnañcassa cittaṃ hoti.**When a mendicant has given up mental corruption in these six cases, their mind inclines to renunciation.*";
P_HTM[6341]="*Nekkhammaparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ kammaniyaṃ khāyati, abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.**A mind imbued with renunciation is declared to be capable of directly knowing anything that can be realized.”*";
P_HTM[6342]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6343]="*6. Saññāsuttaṃ**Consciousness*";
P_HTM[6344]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6345]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññāṇasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for eye consciousness,*";
P_HTM[6346]="*Yo sotaviññāṇasmiṃ …**ear consciousness,*";
P_HTM[6347]="*yo ghānaviññāṇasmiṃ …**nose consciousness,*";
P_HTM[6348]="*yo jivhāviññāṇasmiṃ …**tongue consciousness,*";
P_HTM[6349]="*yo kāyaviññāṇasmiṃ …**body consciousness,*";
P_HTM[6350]="*yo manoviññāṇasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**or mind consciousness is a corruption of the mind.*";
P_HTM[6351]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno imesu chasu ṭhānesu cetaso upakkileso pahīno hoti, nekkhammaninnañcassa cittaṃ hoti.**When a mendicant has given up mental corruption in these six cases, their mind inclines to renunciation.*";
P_HTM[6352]="*Nekkhammaparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ kammaniyaṃ khāyati, abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.**A mind imbued with renunciation is declared to be capable of directly knowing anything that can be realized.”*";
P_HTM[6353]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6354]="*7. Sañcetanāsuttaṃ**Contact*";
P_HTM[6355]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6356]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, cakkhusamphassasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for eye contact,*";
P_HTM[6357]="*Yo sotasamphassasmiṃ …**ear contact,*";
P_HTM[6358]="*yo ghānasamphassasmiṃ …**nose contact,*";
P_HTM[6359]="*yo jivhāsamphassasmiṃ …**tongue contact,*";
P_HTM[6360]="*yo kāyasamphassasmiṃ …**body contact,*";
P_HTM[6361]="*yo manosamphassasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**or mind contact is a corruption of the mind. …”*";
P_HTM[6362]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6363]="*abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6364]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6365]="*8. Taṇhāsuttaṃ**Feeling*";
P_HTM[6366]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6367]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, cakkhusamphassajāya vedanāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for feeling born of eye contact,*";
P_HTM[6368]="*Yo sotasamphassajāya vedanāya …**feeling born of ear contact,*";
P_HTM[6369]="*yo ghānasamphassajāya vedanāya …**feeling born of nose contact,*";
P_HTM[6370]="*yo jivhāsamphassajāya vedanāya …**feeling born of tongue contact,*";
P_HTM[6371]="*yo kāyasamphassajāya vedanāya …**feeling born of body contact,*";
P_HTM[6372]="*yo manosamphassajāya vedanāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**or feeling born of mind contact is a defilement of the mind. …”*";
P_HTM[6373]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6374]="*abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6375]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6376]="*9. Dhātusuttaṃ**Perception*";
P_HTM[6377]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6378]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, rūpasaññāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for perception of sights,*";
P_HTM[6379]="*Yo saddasaññāya …**perception of sounds,*";
P_HTM[6380]="*yo gandhasaññāya …**perception of smells,*";
P_HTM[6381]="*yo rasasaññāya …**perception of tastes,*";
P_HTM[6382]="*yo phoṭṭhabbasaññāya …**perception of touches,*";
P_HTM[6383]="*yo dhammasaññāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**or perception of thoughts is a corruption of the mind. …”*";
P_HTM[6384]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6385]="*abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6386]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6387]="*10. Khandhasuttaṃ**Intention*";
P_HTM[6388]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6389]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, rūpasañcetanāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for intention regarding sights,*";
P_HTM[6390]="*Yo saddasañcetanāya …**intention regarding sounds,*";
P_HTM[6391]="*yo gandhasañcetanāya …**intention regarding smells,*";
P_HTM[6392]="*yo rasasañcetanāya …**intention regarding tastes,*";
P_HTM[6393]="*yo phoṭṭhabbasañcetanāya …**intention regarding touches,*";
P_HTM[6394]="*yo dhammasañcetanāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**or intention regarding thoughts is a corruption of the mind. …”*";
P_HTM[6395]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6396]="*abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6397]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6398]="*1. Vivekajasuttaṃ**Craving*";
P_HTM[6399]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6400]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, rūpataṇhāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for craving for sights,*";
P_HTM[6401]="*Yo saddataṇhāya …**craving for sounds,*";
P_HTM[6402]="*yo gandhataṇhāya …**craving for smells,*";
P_HTM[6403]="*yo rasataṇhāya …**craving for tastes,*";
P_HTM[6404]="*yo phoṭṭhabbataṇhāya …**craving for touches,*";
P_HTM[6405]="*yo dhammataṇhāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**or craving for thoughts is a corruption of the mind. …”*";
P_HTM[6406]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6407]="*abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6408]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6409]="*2. Avitakkasuttaṃ**Elements*";
P_HTM[6410]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6411]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for the earth element,*";
P_HTM[6412]="*Yo āpodhātuyā …**the water element,*";
P_HTM[6413]="*yo tejodhātuyā …**the fire element,*";
P_HTM[6414]="*yo vāyodhātuyā …**the air element,*";
P_HTM[6415]="*yo ākāsadhātuyā …**the space element,*";
P_HTM[6416]="*yo viññāṇadhātuyā chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**or the consciousness element is a corruption of the mind. …”*";
P_HTM[6417]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno imesu chasu ṭhānesu cetaso upakkileso pahīno hoti, nekkhammaninnañcassa cittaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[6418]="*Nekkhammaparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ kammaniyaṃ khāyati, abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6419]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6420]="*3. Pītisuttaṃ**The Aggregates*";
P_HTM[6421]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6422]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, rūpasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso … pe … yo viññāṇasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso.**“Mendicants, desire and greed for form, feeling, perception, choices, or consciousness is a corruption of the mind.*";
P_HTM[6423]="*Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno imesu pañcasu ṭhānesu cetaso upakkileso pahīno hoti, nekkhammaninnañcassa cittaṃ hoti.**When a mendicant has given up mental corruption in these five cases, their mind inclines to renunciation.*";
P_HTM[6424]="*Nekkhammaparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ kammaniyaṃ khāyati, abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti.**A mind imbued with renunciation is declared to be capable of directly knowing anything that can be realized.”*";
P_HTM[6425]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6426]="*Kilesavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6427]="*Cakkhu rūpañca viññāṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6428]="*phasso ca vedanāya ca;* **";
P_HTM[6429]="*Saññā ca cetanā taṇhā,* **";
P_HTM[6430]="*dhātu khandhena te dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[6431]="*Kilesasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on corruptions are complete.*";
P_HTM[6432]="*28. Sāriputtasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6433]="*4. Upekkhāsuttaṃ**Born of Seclusion*";
P_HTM[6434]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā sāriputto sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time Venerable Sāriputta was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6435]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then Venerable Sāriputta robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms.*";
P_HTM[6436]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena andhavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya.**He wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Dark Forest,*";
P_HTM[6437]="*Andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi.**plunged deep into it, and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[6438]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena jetavanaṃ anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāmo tenupasaṅkami.**Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta came out of retreat and went to Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6439]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Venerable Ānanda saw him coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[6440]="*Disvāna āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6441]="*“vippasannāni kho te, āvuso sāriputta, indriyāni; parisuddho mukhavaṇṇo pariyodāto.**“Reverend Sāriputta, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright.*";
P_HTM[6442]="*Katamenāyasmā sāriputto ajja vihārena vihāsī”ti?**What meditation were you practicing today?”*";
P_HTM[6443]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**“Reverend, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6444]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, na evaṃ hoti:**But it didn’t occur to me:*";
P_HTM[6445]="*‘ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ paṭhamā jhānā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the first absorption’ or ‘I have entered the first absorption’ or ‘I am emerging from the first absorption’.”*";
P_HTM[6446]="*Tathā hi panāyasmato sāriputtassa dīgharattaṃ ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā susamūhatā.**“That must be because Venerable Sāriputta has long ago totally eradicated ego, possessiveness, and the underlying tendency to conceit.*";
P_HTM[6447]="*Tasmā āyasmato sāriputtassa na evaṃ hoti:**That’s why it didn’t occur to you:*";
P_HTM[6448]="*“‘ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ paṭhamā jhānā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the first absorption’ or ‘I have entered the first absorption’ or ‘I am emerging from the first absorption’.”*";
P_HTM[6449]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6450]="*5. Ākāsānañcāyatanasuttaṃ**Without Placing the Mind*";
P_HTM[6451]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6452]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando … pe … āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**Venerable Ānanda saw Venerable Sāriputta and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6453]="*“vippasannāni kho te, āvuso sāriputta, indriyāni; parisuddho mukhavaṇṇo pariyodāto.**“Reverend Sāriputta, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright.*";
P_HTM[6454]="*Katamenāyasmā sāriputto ajja vihārena vihāsī”ti?**What meditation were you practicing today?”*";
P_HTM[6455]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**“Reverend, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled, I entered and remained in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6456]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, na evaṃ hoti:**But it didn’t occur to me:*";
P_HTM[6457]="*‘ahaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ dutiyā jhānā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the second absorption’ or ‘I have entered the second absorption’ or ‘I am emerging from the second absorption’.”*";
P_HTM[6458]="*Tathā hi panāyasmato sāriputtassa dīgharattaṃ ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā susamūhatā.**“That must be because Venerable Sāriputta has long ago totally eradicated ego, possessiveness, and the underlying tendency to conceit.*";
P_HTM[6459]="*Tasmā āyasmato sāriputtassa na evaṃ hoti:**That’s why it didn’t occur to you:*";
P_HTM[6460]="*“‘ahaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ dutiyā jhānā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the second absorption’ or ‘I have entered the second absorption’ or ‘I am emerging from the second absorption’.”*";
P_HTM[6461]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6462]="*6. Viññāṇañcāyatanasuttaṃ**Rapture*";
P_HTM[6463]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6464]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando … pe …**Venerable Ānanda saw Venerable Sāriputta and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6465]="*“vippasannāni kho te, āvuso sāriputta, indriyāni; parisuddho mukhavaṇṇo pariyodāto.**“Reverend Sāriputta, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright.*";
P_HTM[6466]="*Katamenāyasmā sāriputto ajja vihārena vihāsī”ti?**What meditation were you practicing today?”*";
P_HTM[6467]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihāsiṃ sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedemi; yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**“Reverend, with the fading away of rapture, I entered and remained in the third absorption, where I meditated with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[6468]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, na evaṃ hoti:**But it didn’t occur to me:*";
P_HTM[6469]="*‘ahaṃ tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ tatiyā jhānā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the third absorption’ or ‘I have entered the third absorption’ or ‘I am emerging from the third absorption’.”*";
P_HTM[6470]="*Tathā hi panāyasmato sāriputtassa dīgharattaṃ ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā susamūhatā.**“That must be because Venerable Sāriputta has long ago totally eradicated ego, possessiveness, and the underlying tendency to conceit.*";
P_HTM[6471]="*Tasmā āyasmato sāriputtassa na evaṃ hoti:**That’s why it didn’t occur to you:*";
P_HTM[6472]="*“‘ahaṃ tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ tatiyā jhānā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the third absorption’ or ‘I have entered the third absorption’ or ‘I am emerging from the third absorption’.”*";
P_HTM[6473]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6474]="*7. Ākiñcaññāyatanasuttaṃ**Equanimity*";
P_HTM[6475]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6476]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando … pe …**Venerable Ānanda saw Venerable Sāriputta and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6477]="*“vippasannāni kho te, āvuso sāriputta, indriyāni; parisuddho mukhavaṇṇo pariyodāto.**“Reverend Sāriputta, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright.*";
P_HTM[6478]="*Katamenāyasmā sāriputto ajja vihārena vihāsī”ti?**What meditation were you practicing today?”*";
P_HTM[6479]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**“Reverend, with the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, I entered and remained in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[6480]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, na evaṃ hoti:**But it didn’t occur to me:*";
P_HTM[6481]="*‘ahaṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ catutthā jhānā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the fourth absorption’ or ‘I have entered the fourth absorption’ or ‘I am emerging from the fourth absorption’.”*";
P_HTM[6482]="*Tathā hi panāyasmato sāriputtassa dīgharattaṃ ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā susamūhatā.**“That must be because Venerable Sāriputta has long ago totally eradicated ego, possessiveness, and the underlying tendency to conceit.*";
P_HTM[6483]="*Tasmā āyasmato sāriputtassa na evaṃ hoti:**That’s why it didn’t occur to you:*";
P_HTM[6484]="*“‘ahaṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ catutthā jhānā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the fourth absorption’ or ‘I have entered the fourth absorption’ or ‘I am emerging from the fourth absorption’.”*";
P_HTM[6485]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6486]="*8. Nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasuttaṃ**The Dimension of Infinite Space*";
P_HTM[6487]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6488]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando … pe …**Venerable Ānanda saw Venerable Sāriputta …*";
P_HTM[6489]="*“idhāhaṃ, āvuso, sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ananto ākāsoti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāmi … pe …**“Reverend, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, I entered and remained in the dimension of infinite space. …” …*";
P_HTM[6490]="*vuṭṭhitoti vā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6491]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6492]="*9. Nirodhasamāpattisuttaṃ**The Dimension of Infinite Consciousness*";
P_HTM[6493]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6494]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando … pe …**Venerable Ānanda saw Venerable Sāriputta …*";
P_HTM[6495]="*“idhāhaṃ, āvuso, sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma anantaṃ viññāṇanti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāmi … pe …**“Reverend, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, I entered and remained in the dimension of infinite consciousness. …” …*";
P_HTM[6496]="*vuṭṭhitoti vā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6497]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6498]="*10. Sūcimukhīsuttaṃ**The Dimension of Nothingness*";
P_HTM[6499]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6500]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto … pe …**Venerable Ānanda saw Venerable Sāriputta …*";
P_HTM[6501]="*“idhāhaṃ, āvuso, sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma, natthi kiñcīti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāmi … pe …**“Reverend, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, I entered and remained in the dimension of nothingness. …” …*";
P_HTM[6502]="*vuṭṭhitoti vā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6503]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6504]="*1. Suddhikasuttaṃ**The Dimension of Neither Perception Nor Non*";
P_HTM[6505]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6506]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto … pe …**Venerable Ānanda saw Venerable Sāriputta …*";
P_HTM[6507]="*“idhāhaṃ, āvuso, ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāmi … pe …**“Reverend, going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, I entered and remained in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. …” …*";
P_HTM[6508]="*vuṭṭhitoti vā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6509]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6510]="*2. Paṇītatarasuttaṃ**The Attainment of Cessation*";
P_HTM[6511]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6512]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto … pe ….**Venerable Ānanda saw Venerable Sāriputta …*";
P_HTM[6513]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**“Reverend, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, I entered and remained in the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[6514]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, na evaṃ hoti:**But it didn’t occur to me:*";
P_HTM[6515]="*‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I have entered the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I am emerging from the cessation of perception and feeling’.”*";
P_HTM[6516]="*Tathā hi panāyasmato sāriputtassa dīgharattaṃ ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā susamūhatā.**“That must be because Venerable Sāriputta has long ago totally eradicated ego, possessiveness, and the underlying tendency to conceit.*";
P_HTM[6517]="*Tasmā āyasmato sāriputtassa na evaṃ hoti:**That’s why it didn’t occur to you:*";
P_HTM[6518]="*“‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjāmī’ti vā ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpanno’ti vā ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhā vuṭṭhito’ti vā”ti.**‘I am entering the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I have entered the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I am emerging from the cessation of perception and feeling’.”*";
P_HTM[6519]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6520]="*3. Uposathasuttaṃ**With Sucimukhī*";
P_HTM[6521]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā sāriputto rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time Venerable Sāriputta was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[6522]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahe piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then he robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Rājagaha for alms.*";
P_HTM[6523]="*Rājagahe sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ aññataraṃ kuṭṭamūlaṃ nissāya paribhuñjati.**After wandering indiscriminately for alms-food in Rājagaha, he ate his alms-food by a wall.*";
P_HTM[6524]="*Atha kho sucimukhī paribbājikā yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**Then the wanderer Sucimukhī went up to Venerable Sāriputta and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6525]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, samaṇa, adhomukho bhuñjasī”ti?**“Ascetic, do you eat facing downwards?”*";
P_HTM[6526]="*“Na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, adhomukho bhuñjāmī”ti.**“No, sister.”*";
P_HTM[6527]="*“Tena hi, samaṇa, ubbhamukho bhuñjasī”ti?**“Well then, do you eat facing upwards?”*";
P_HTM[6528]="*“Na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, ubbhamukho bhuñjāmī”ti.**“No, sister.”*";
P_HTM[6529]="*“Tena hi, samaṇa, disāmukho bhuñjasī”ti?**“Well then, do you eat facing the cardinal directions?”*";
P_HTM[6530]="*“Na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, disāmukho bhuñjāmī”ti.**“No, sister.”*";
P_HTM[6531]="*“Tena hi, samaṇa, vidisāmukho bhuñjasī”ti?**“Well then, do you eat facing the intermediate directions?”*";
P_HTM[6532]="*“Na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, vidisāmukho bhuñjāmī”ti.**“No, sister.”*";
P_HTM[6533]="*“‘Kiṃ nu, samaṇa, adhomukho bhuñjasī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, adhomukho bhuñjāmī’ti vadesi.**“When asked if you eat facing all these directions, you answer ‘no, sister’.*";
P_HTM[6534]="*‘Tena hi, samaṇa, ubbhamukho bhuñjasī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, ubbhamukho bhuñjāmī’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[6535]="*‘Tena hi, samaṇa, disāmukho bhuñjasī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, disāmukho bhuñjāmī’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[6536]="*‘Tena hi, samaṇa, vidisāmukho bhuñjasī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na khvāhaṃ, bhagini, vidisāmukho bhuñjāmī’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[6537]="*Kathañcarahi, samaṇa, bhuñjasī”ti?**How exactly do you eat, ascetic?”*";
P_HTM[6538]="*“Ye hi keci, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā vatthuvijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappenti, ime vuccanti, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ‘adhomukhā bhuñjantī’ti.**“Sister, those ascetics and brahmins who earn a living by geomancy—an unworthy branch of knowledge, a wrong livelihood—are said to eat facing downwards.*";
P_HTM[6539]="*Ye hi keci, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā nakkhattavijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappenti, ime vuccanti, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ‘ubbhamukhā bhuñjantī’ti.**Those ascetics and brahmins who earn a living by astrology—an unworthy branch of knowledge, a wrong livelihood—are said to eat facing upwards.*";
P_HTM[6540]="*Ye hi keci, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappenti, ime vuccanti, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ‘disāmukhā bhuñjantī’ti.**Those ascetics and brahmins who earn a living by running errands and messages—a wrong livelihood—are said to eat facing the cardinal directions.*";
P_HTM[6541]="*Ye hi keci, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā aṅgavijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappenti, ime vuccanti, bhagini, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ‘vidisāmukhā bhuñjantī’ti.**Those ascetics and brahmins who earn a living by palmistry—an unworthy branch of knowledge, a wrong livelihood—are said to eat facing the intermediate directions.*";
P_HTM[6542]="*So khvāhaṃ, bhagini, na vatthuvijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappemi, na nakkhattavijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappemi, na dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappemi, na aṅgavijjātiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvikaṃ kappemi.**I don’t earn a living by any of these means.*";
P_HTM[6543]="*Dhammena bhikkhaṃ pariyesāmi;**I seek alms in a principled manner,*";
P_HTM[6544]="*dhammena bhikkhaṃ pariyesitvā bhuñjāmī”ti.**and I eat it in a principled manner.”*";
P_HTM[6545]="*Atha kho sucimukhī paribbājikā rājagahe rathiyāya rathiyaṃ, siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamārocesi:**Then Sucimukhī the wanderer went around Rājagaha from street to street, from square to square, and announced:*";
P_HTM[6546]="*“dhammikaṃ samaṇā sakyaputtiyā āhāraṃ āhārenti;**“The Sakyan ascetics eat food in a principled manner!*";
P_HTM[6547]="*anavajjaṃ samaṇā sakyaputtiyā āhāraṃ āhārenti.**The Sakyan ascetics eat food blamelessly!*";
P_HTM[6548]="*Detha samaṇānaṃ sakyaputtiyānaṃ piṇḍan”ti.**Give almsfood to the Sakyan ascetics!”*";
P_HTM[6549]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6550]="*Sāriputtavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6551]="*Vivekajaṃ avitakkaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6552]="*pīti upekkhā catutthakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6553]="*Ākāsañceva viññāṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6554]="*ākiñcaṃ nevasaññinā;* **";
P_HTM[6555]="*Nirodho navamo vutto,* **";
P_HTM[6556]="*dasamaṃ sūcimukhī cāti.* **";
P_HTM[6557]="*Sāriputtasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on Sāriputta are complete.*";
P_HTM[6558]="*29. Nāgasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6559]="*4. Dutiyauposathasuttaṃ**Plain Version*";
P_HTM[6560]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6561]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, nāgayoniyo.**“Mendicants, dragons reproduce in these four ways.*";
P_HTM[6562]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6563]="*Aṇḍajā nāgā, jalābujā nāgā, saṃsedajā nāgā, opapātikā nāgā—**Dragons are born from eggs, from a womb, from moisture, or spontaneously.*";
P_HTM[6564]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso nāgayoniyo”ti.**These are the four ways that dragons reproduce.”*";
P_HTM[6565]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6566]="*5. Tatiyauposathasuttaṃ**Better*";
P_HTM[6567]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6568]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, nāgayoniyo.**“Mendicants, dragons reproduce in these four ways.*";
P_HTM[6569]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6570]="*Aṇḍajā nāgā, jalābujā nāgā, saṃsedajā nāgā, opapātikā nāgā.**Dragons are born from an egg, from a womb, from moisture, or spontaneously.*";
P_HTM[6571]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, aṇḍajehi nāgehi jalābujā ca saṃsedajā ca opapātikā ca nāgā paṇītatarā.**Of these, dragons born from a womb, from moisture, or spontaneously are better than those born from an egg.*";
P_HTM[6572]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, aṇḍajehi ca jalābujehi ca nāgehi saṃsedajā ca opapātikā ca nāgā paṇītatarā.**Dragons born from moisture or spontaneously are better than those born from an egg or from a womb.*";
P_HTM[6573]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, aṇḍajehi ca jalābujehi ca saṃsedajehi ca nāgehi opapātikā nāgā paṇītatarā.**Dragons born spontaneously are better than those born from an egg, from a womb, or from moisture.*";
P_HTM[6574]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso nāgayoniyo”ti.**These are the four ways that dragons reproduce.”*";
P_HTM[6575]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6576]="*6. Catutthauposathasuttaṃ**Sabbath*";
P_HTM[6577]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6578]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6579]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce aṇḍajā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why some egg-born dragons keep the sabbath, having transformed their bodies?”*";
P_HTM[6580]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekaccānaṃ aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ evaṃ hoti:**“Mendicant, it’s when some egg-born dragons think:*";
P_HTM[6581]="*‘mayaṃ kho pubbe kāyena dvayakārino ahumha, vācāya dvayakārino, manasā dvayakārino.**‘In the past we did both kinds of deeds by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6582]="*Te mayaṃ kāyena dvayakārino, vācāya dvayakārino, manasā dvayakārino, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapannā.**When the body broke up, after death, we were reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons.*";
P_HTM[6583]="*Sacajja mayaṃ kāyena sucaritaṃ careyyāma, vācāya sucaritaṃ careyyāma, manasā sucaritaṃ careyyāma, evaṃ mayaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyāma.**If today we do good things by body, speech, and mind, when the body breaks up, after death, we may be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[6584]="*Handa mayaṃ etarahi kāyena sucaritaṃ carāma, vācāya sucaritaṃ carāma, manasā sucaritaṃ carāmā’ti.**Come, let us do good things by way of body, speech, and mind.’*";
P_HTM[6585]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena m’idhekacce aṇḍajā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why some egg-born dragons keep the sabbath, having transformed their bodies.”*";
P_HTM[6586]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6587]="*7. Sutasuttaṃ**Sabbath (2nd)*";
P_HTM[6588]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6589]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[6590]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce jalābujā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why some womb-born dragons keep the sabbath, having transformed their bodies?”*";
P_HTM[6591]="*(Sabbaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(All should be told in full.)*";
P_HTM[6592]="*“Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena m’idhekacce jalābujā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6593]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6594]="*8. Dutiyasutasuttaṃ**Sabbath (3rd)*";
P_HTM[6595]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6596]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6597]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce saṃsedajā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why some moisture-born dragons keep the sabbath, having transformed their bodies?”*";
P_HTM[6598]="*(Sabbaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(All should be told in full.)*";
P_HTM[6599]="*“Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena m’idhekacce saṃsedajā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6600]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6601]="*9. Tatiyasutasuttaṃ**Sabbath (4th)*";
P_HTM[6602]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6603]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6604]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena m’idhekacce opapātikā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why some spontaneously-born dragons keep the sabbath, having transformed their bodies?”*";
P_HTM[6605]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekaccānaṃ opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ evaṃ hoti:**(All should be told in full.)*";
P_HTM[6606]="*‘mayaṃ kho pubbe kāyena dvayakārino ahumha, vācāya dvayakārino, manasā dvayakārino.* **";
P_HTM[6607]="*Te mayaṃ kāyena dvayakārino, vācāya dvayakārino, manasā dvayakārino, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapannā.* **";
P_HTM[6608]="*Sacajja mayaṃ kāyena sucaritaṃ careyyāma, vācāya … manasā sucaritaṃ careyyāma, evaṃ mayaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyāma.* **";
P_HTM[6609]="*Handa mayaṃ etarahi kāyena sucaritaṃ carāma, vācāya … manasā sucaritaṃ carāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6610]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena m’idhekacce opapātikā nāgā uposathaṃ upavasanti vossaṭṭhakāyā ca bhavantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6611]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6612]="*10. Catutthasutasuttaṃ**They’ve Heard*";
P_HTM[6613]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6614]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6615]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons?”*";
P_HTM[6616]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena dvayakārī hoti, vācāya dvayakārī hoti, manasā dvayakārī hoti.**“Mendicant, it’s when someone does both kinds of deeds by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6617]="*Tassa sutaṃ hoti:**And they’ve heard:*";
P_HTM[6618]="*‘aṇḍajā nāgā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti.**‘The egg-born dragons are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’*";
P_HTM[6619]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[6620]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti.**‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons!’*";
P_HTM[6621]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons.*";
P_HTM[6622]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons.”*";
P_HTM[6623]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6624]="*11-20. Aṇḍajadānūpakārasuttadasakaṃ**They’ve Heard (2nd)*";
P_HTM[6625]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6626]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6627]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā jalābujānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the womb-born dragons?”*";
P_HTM[6628]="*… pe …**(All should be told in full.)*";
P_HTM[6629]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā jalābujānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6630]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6631]="*21-50. Jalābujādidānūpakārasuttattiṃsakaṃ**They’ve Heard (3rd)*";
P_HTM[6632]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6633]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6634]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā saṃsedajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the moisture-born dragons?”*";
P_HTM[6635]="*… pe …**(All should be told in full.)*";
P_HTM[6636]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā saṃsedajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6637]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6638]="*1. Suddhikasuttaṃ**They’ve Heard (4th)*";
P_HTM[6639]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6640]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6641]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the spontaneously-born dragons?”*";
P_HTM[6642]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena dvayakārī hoti, vācāya dvayakārī, manasā dvayakārī.**(All should be told in full.)*";
P_HTM[6643]="*Tassa sutaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[6644]="*‘opapātikā nāgā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6645]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[6646]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6647]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6648]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6649]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6650]="*2. Harantisuttaṃ**11–20. Aṇḍajadānūpakārasuttadasaka*";
P_HTM[6651]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6652]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons?”*";
P_HTM[6653]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena dvayakārī hoti, vācāya dvayakārī, manasā dvayakārī.**“Mendicant, it’s when someone does both kinds of deeds by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6654]="*Tassa sutaṃ hoti:**And they’ve heard:*";
P_HTM[6655]="*‘aṇḍajā nāgā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti.**‘The egg-born dragons are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’*";
P_HTM[6656]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[6657]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti.**‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons!’*";
P_HTM[6658]="*So annaṃ deti.**They give food …*";
P_HTM[6659]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6660]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu … pe … upapajjatīti … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6661]="*so pānaṃ deti … pe …**drink …*";
P_HTM[6662]="*vatthaṃ deti … pe …**clothing …*";
P_HTM[6663]="*yānaṃ deti … pe …**a vehicle …*";
P_HTM[6664]="*mālaṃ deti … pe …**a garland …*";
P_HTM[6665]="*gandhaṃ deti … pe …**fragrance …*";
P_HTM[6666]="*vilepanaṃ deti … pe …**makeup …*";
P_HTM[6667]="*seyyaṃ deti … pe …**a bed …*";
P_HTM[6668]="*āvasathaṃ deti … pe …**a house …*";
P_HTM[6669]="*padīpeyyaṃ deti.**a lamp.*";
P_HTM[6670]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons.*";
P_HTM[6671]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born dragons.”*";
P_HTM[6672]="*Vīsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6673]="*3. Dvayakārīsuttaṃ**21–50. Jalābujādidānūpakārasuttattiṃsaka*";
P_HTM[6674]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6675]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6676]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā jalābujānaṃ nāgānaṃ … pe …**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the womb-born dragons …*";
P_HTM[6677]="*saṃsedajānaṃ nāgānaṃ … pe …**moisture-born dragons …*";
P_HTM[6678]="*opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?**spontaneously-born dragons?”*";
P_HTM[6679]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena dvayakārī hoti, vācāya dvayakārī, manasā dvayakārī.**“Mendicant, it’s when someone does both kinds of deeds by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6680]="*Tassa sutaṃ hoti:**And they’ve heard:*";
P_HTM[6681]="*‘opapātikā nāgā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti.**‘The spontaneously-born dragons are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’*";
P_HTM[6682]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[6683]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti.**‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the spontaneously-born dragons!’*";
P_HTM[6684]="*So annaṃ deti … pe …**They give food …*";
P_HTM[6685]="*pānaṃ deti … pe …**drink …*";
P_HTM[6686]="*padīpeyyaṃ deti.**a lamp.*";
P_HTM[6687]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the spontaneously-born dragons.*";
P_HTM[6688]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ nāgānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the spontaneously-born dragons.”*";
P_HTM[6689]="*(Iminā peyyālena dasa dasa suttantā kātabbā.**(Each set of ten discourses of this series should be treated in the same way.)*";
P_HTM[6690]="*Evaṃ catūsu yonīsu cattālīsaṃ veyyākaraṇā honti.* **";
P_HTM[6691]="*Purimehi pana dasahi suttantehi saha honti paṇṇāsasuttantāti.)* **";
P_HTM[6692]="*Nāgavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6693]="*Suddhikaṃ paṇītataraṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6694]="*caturo ca uposathā;* **";
P_HTM[6695]="*Tassa sutaṃ caturo ca,* **";
P_HTM[6696]="*dānūpakārā ca tālīsaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6697]="*Paṇṇāsa piṇḍato suttā,* **";
P_HTM[6698]="*nāgamhi suppakāsitāti.* **";
P_HTM[6699]="*Nāgasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on dragons are complete.*";
P_HTM[6700]="*30. Supaṇṇasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6701]="*4-6. Dutiyādidvayakārīsuttattikaṃ**Plain Version*";
P_HTM[6702]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6703]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, supaṇṇayoniyo.**“Mendicants, phoenixes reproduce in these four ways.*";
P_HTM[6704]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6705]="*Aṇḍajā supaṇṇā, jalābujā supaṇṇā, saṃsedajā supaṇṇā, opapātikā supaṇṇā—**Phoenixes are born from eggs, from a womb, from moisture, or spontaneously.*";
P_HTM[6706]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso supaṇṇayoniyo”ti.**These are the four ways that phoenixes reproduce.”*";
P_HTM[6707]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6708]="*7-16. Aṇḍajadānūpakārasuttadasakaṃ**They Carry Off*";
P_HTM[6709]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6710]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, supaṇṇayoniyo.**“Mendicants, phoenixes reproduce in these four ways.*";
P_HTM[6711]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[6712]="*Aṇḍajā … pe …**Phoenixes are born from eggs, from a womb, from moisture, or spontaneously.*";
P_HTM[6713]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso supaṇṇayoniyo.**These are the four ways that phoenixes reproduce.*";
P_HTM[6714]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, aṇḍajā supaṇṇā aṇḍajeva nāge haranti, na jalābuje, na saṃsedaje, na opapātike.**Of these, phoenixes born from an egg can only carry off dragons born from an egg, not those born from a womb, from moisture, or spontaneously.*";
P_HTM[6715]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, jalābujā supaṇṇā aṇḍaje ca jalābuje ca nāge haranti, na saṃsedaje, na opapātike.**Phoenixes born from a womb can carry off dragons born from an egg or from a womb, but not those born from moisture or spontaneously.*";
P_HTM[6716]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, saṃsedajā supaṇṇā aṇḍaje ca jalābuje ca saṃsedaje ca nāge haranti, na opapātike.**Phoenixes born from moisture can carry off dragons born from an egg, from a womb, or from moisture, but not those born spontaneously.*";
P_HTM[6717]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, opapātikā supaṇṇā aṇḍaje ca jalābuje ca saṃsedaje ca opapātike ca nāge haranti.**Phoenixes born spontaneously can carry off dragons born from an egg, from a womb, from moisture, or spontaneously.*";
P_HTM[6718]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso supaṇṇayoniyo”ti.**These are the four ways that phoenixes reproduce.”*";
P_HTM[6719]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6720]="*17-46. Jalābujādidānūpakārasuttatiṃsakaṃ**Both Kinds of Deeds*";
P_HTM[6721]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6722]="*Aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[6723]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born phoenixes?”*";
P_HTM[6724]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena dvayakārī hoti, vācāya dvayakārī, manasā dvayakārī.**“Mendicant, it’s when someone does both kinds of deeds by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6725]="*Tassa sutaṃ hoti:**And they’ve heard:*";
P_HTM[6726]="*‘aṇḍajā supaṇṇā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti.**‘The egg-born phoenixes are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’*";
P_HTM[6727]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[6728]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti.**‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the egg-born phoenixes!’*";
P_HTM[6729]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the egg-born phoenixes.*";
P_HTM[6730]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born phoenixes.”*";
P_HTM[6731]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6732]="*1. Suddhikasuttaṃ**4–6. Dutiyādidvayakārīsuttattika*";
P_HTM[6733]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6734]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6735]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā jalābujānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ … pe …**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the womb-born phoenixes …*";
P_HTM[6736]="*saṃsedajānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ … pe …**moisture-born phoenixes …*";
P_HTM[6737]="*opapātikānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?**or spontaneously-born phoenixes?”*";
P_HTM[6738]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena dvayakārī hoti, vācāya dvayakārī, manasā dvayakārī.**(All should be told in full.)*";
P_HTM[6739]="*Tassa sutaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[6740]="*‘opapātikā supaṇṇā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6741]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[6742]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6743]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.* **";
P_HTM[6744]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā opapātikānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6745]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6746]="*2. Sucaritasuttaṃ**7–16. Aṇḍajadānūpakārasuttadasaka*";
P_HTM[6747]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
