P_HTM[6749]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born phoenixes?”*";
P_HTM[6750]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena dvayakārī hoti, vācāya dvayakārī, manasā dvayakārī.**“Mendicant, it’s when someone does both kinds of deeds by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[6751]="*Tassa sutaṃ hoti:**And they’ve heard:*";
P_HTM[6752]="*‘aṇḍajā supaṇṇā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti.**‘The egg-born phoenixes are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’*";
P_HTM[6753]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[6754]="*‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti.**‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the egg-born phoenixes!’*";
P_HTM[6755]="*So annaṃ deti … pe …**They give food …*";
P_HTM[6756]="*pānaṃ deti …**drink …*";
P_HTM[6757]="*vatthaṃ deti …**clothing …*";
P_HTM[6758]="*yānaṃ deti …**a vehicle …*";
P_HTM[6759]="*mālaṃ deti …**a garland …*";
P_HTM[6760]="*gandhaṃ deti …**fragrance …*";
P_HTM[6761]="*vilepanaṃ deti …**makeup …*";
P_HTM[6762]="*seyyaṃ deti …**a bed …*";
P_HTM[6763]="*āvasathaṃ deti …**a house …*";
P_HTM[6764]="*padīpeyyaṃ deti.**a lamp.*";
P_HTM[6765]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the egg-born phoenixes.*";
P_HTM[6766]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā aṇḍajānaṃ supaṇṇānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the egg-born phoenixes.”*";
P_HTM[6767]="*Soḷasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6768]="*3. Mūlagandhadātāsuttaṃ**17–46. Jalābujadānūpakārasutta*";
P_HTM[6769]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
