P_HTM[6933]="*32. Valāhakasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6934]="*13-52. Uṇhavalāhakadānūpakārasuttacālīsakaṃ**Plain Version*";
P_HTM[6935]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6936]="*“Valāhakakāyike vo, bhikkhave, deve desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you about the gods of the clouds.*";
P_HTM[6937]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[6938]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, valāhakakāyikā devā?**And what are the gods of the clouds?*";
P_HTM[6939]="*Santi, bhikkhave, sītavalāhakā devā;**There are gods of the cool clouds,*";
P_HTM[6940]="*santi uṇhavalāhakā devā;**warm clouds,*";
P_HTM[6941]="*santi abbhavalāhakā devā;**thunder clouds,*";
P_HTM[6942]="*santi vātavalāhakā devā;**windy clouds,*";
P_HTM[6943]="*santi vassavalāhakā devā—**and rainy clouds.*";
P_HTM[6944]="*ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, ‘valāhakakāyikā devā’”ti.**These are called the gods of the clouds.”*";
P_HTM[6945]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6946]="*53. Sītavalāhakasuttaṃ**Good Conduct*";
