P_HTM[7001]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yenekadā uṇhaṃ hotī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why sometimes it becomes warm?”*";
P_HTM[7002]="*“Santi, bhikkhu, uṇhavalāhakā nāma devā.**“Mendicant, there are what are called gods of the warm clouds.*";
P_HTM[7003]="*Tesaṃ yadā evaṃ hoti:**Sometimes they think:*";
P_HTM[7004]="*‘yannūna mayaṃ sakāya ratiyā vaseyyāmā’ti, tesaṃ taṃ cetopaṇidhimanvāya uṇhaṃ hoti.**‘Why don’t we revel in our own kind of enjoyment?’ Then, in accordance with their wish, it becomes warm.*";
P_HTM[7005]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yenekadā uṇhaṃ hotī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why sometimes it becomes warm.”*";
P_HTM[7006]="*Catupaññāsamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7007]="*1. Rūpaaññāṇasuttaṃ**Gods of the Storm Clouds*";
P_HTM[7008]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7009]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7010]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yenekadā abbhaṃ hotī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why sometimes it becomes stormy?”*";
P_HTM[7011]="*“Santi, bhikkhu, abbhavalāhakā nāma devā.**“Mendicant, there are what are called gods of the storm clouds.*";
P_HTM[7012]="*Tesaṃ yadā evaṃ hoti:**Sometimes they think:*";
P_HTM[7013]="*‘yannūna mayaṃ sakāya ratiyā vaseyyāmā’ti, tesaṃ taṃ cetopaṇidhimanvāya abbhaṃ hoti.**‘Why don’t we revel in our own kind of enjoyment?’ Then, in accordance with their wish, it becomes stormy.*";
P_HTM[7014]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yenekadā abbhaṃ hotī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why sometimes it becomes stormy.”*";
P_HTM[7015]="*Pañcapaññāsamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7016]="*2. Vedanāaññāṇasuttaṃ**Gods of the Windy Clouds*";
P_HTM[7017]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7018]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7019]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yenekadā vāto hotī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why sometimes it becomes windy?”*";
P_HTM[7020]="*“Santi, bhikkhu, vātavalāhakā nāma devā.**“Mendicant, there are what are called gods of the windy clouds.*";
P_HTM[7021]="*Tesaṃ yadā evaṃ hoti:**Sometimes they think:*";
P_HTM[7022]="*‘yannūna mayaṃ sakāya ratiyā vaseyyāmā’ti, tesaṃ taṃ cetopaṇidhimanvāya vāto hoti.**‘Why don’t we revel in our own kind of enjoyment?’ Then, in accordance with their wish, it becomes windy.*";
P_HTM[7023]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yenekadā vāto hotī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why sometimes it becomes windy.”*";
P_HTM[7024]="*Chappaññāsamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7025]="*3. Saññāaññāṇasuttaṃ**Gods of the Rainy Clouds*";
P_HTM[7026]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7027]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7028]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yenekadā devo vassatī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why sometimes it rains?”*";
P_HTM[7029]="*“Santi, bhikkhu, vassavalāhakā nāma devā.**“Mendicant, there are what are called gods of the rainy clouds.*";
P_HTM[7030]="*Tesaṃ yadā evaṃ hoti:**Sometimes they think:*";
P_HTM[7031]="*‘yannūna mayaṃ sakāya ratiyā vaseyyāmā’ti, tesaṃ taṃ cetopaṇidhimanvāya devo vassati.**‘Why don’t we revel in our own kind of enjoyment?’ Then, in accordance with their wish, it becomes rainy.*";
P_HTM[7032]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yenekadā devo vassatī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why sometimes it rains.”*";
P_HTM[7033]="*Sattapaññāsamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7034]="*Sattapaññāsasuttantaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7035]="*Valāhakavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[7036]="*Suddhikaṃ sucaritañca,* **";
P_HTM[7037]="*dānūpakārapaññāsaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7038]="*Sītaṃ uṇhañca abbhañca,* **";
P_HTM[7039]="*vātavassavalāhakāti.* **";
P_HTM[7040]="*Valāhakasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on gods of the clouds are complete.*";
P_HTM[7041]="*33. Vacchagottasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[7042]="*4. Saṅkhāraaññāṇasuttaṃ**Not Knowing Form*";
P_HTM[7043]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7044]="*Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[7045]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7046]="*“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo, yānimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**“What is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why these various misconceptions arise in the world? That is:*";
P_HTM[7047]="*sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā, antavā lokoti vā, anantavā lokoti vā, taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīranti vā, aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīranti vā, hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā, hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā, neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”ti?**the world is eternal, or not eternal, or finite, or infinite; the soul and the body are the same thing, or they are different things; after death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist.”*";
P_HTM[7048]="*“Rūpe kho, vaccha, aññāṇā, rūpasamudaye aññāṇā, rūpanirodhe aññāṇā, rūpanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya aññāṇā;**“Vaccha, it is because of not knowing form, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation*";
P_HTM[7049]="*evamimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**that these various misconceptions arise in the world.*";
P_HTM[7050]="*sassato lokoti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7051]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vāti.* **";
P_HTM[7052]="*Ayaṃ kho, vaccha, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yānimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**This is the cause, this is the reason.”*";
P_HTM[7053]="*sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7054]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7055]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7056]="*5. Viññāṇaaññāṇasuttaṃ**Not Knowing Feeling*";
P_HTM[7057]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7058]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the wanderer Vacchagotta said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7059]="*“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo, yānimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**“What is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why these various misconceptions arise in the world? That is:*";
P_HTM[7060]="*sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā … pe …**the cosmos is eternal, or not eternal …*";
P_HTM[7061]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”ti?**after death, a Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist.”*";
P_HTM[7062]="*“Vedanāya kho, vaccha, aññāṇā, vedanāsamudaye aññāṇā, vedanānirodhe aññāṇā, vedanānirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya aññāṇā;**“Vaccha, it is because of not knowing feeling, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation*";
P_HTM[7063]="*evamimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**that these various misconceptions arise in the world.*";
P_HTM[7064]="*sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7065]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vāti.* **";
P_HTM[7066]="*Ayaṃ kho, vaccha, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yānimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**This is the cause, this is the reason.”*";
P_HTM[7067]="*sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7068]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7069]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
