P_HTM[7075]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7076]="*“Saññāya kho, vaccha, aññāṇā, saññāsamudaye aññāṇā, saññānirodhe aññāṇā, saññānirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya aññāṇā;**“Vaccha, it is because of not knowing perception, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation …”*";
P_HTM[7077]="*evamimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—* **";
P_HTM[7078]="*sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7079]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vāti.* **";
P_HTM[7080]="*Ayaṃ kho, vaccha, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yānimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—* **";
P_HTM[7081]="*sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7082]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7083]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7084]="*11-15. Rūpaanabhisamayādisuttapañcakaṃ**Not Knowing Choices*";
P_HTM[7085]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7086]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the wanderer Vacchagotta said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7087]="*“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo, yānimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**“What is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why these various misconceptions arise in the world? …”*";
