P_HTM[7168]="*55. Viññāṇaappaccakkhakammasuttaṃ**41–45. Rūpaasamapekkhaṇādisuttapañcaka*";
P_HTM[7169]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7170]="*“Rūpe kho, vaccha, asamapekkhaṇā … pe … viññāṇe kho, vaccha, asamapekkhaṇā … pe ….**“Vaccha, it is because of not examining form …”*";
P_HTM[7171]="*Pañcacattālīsamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7172]="*1. Samādhimūlakasamāpattisuttaṃ**46–50. Rūpaappaccupekkhaṇādisuttapañcaka*";
P_HTM[7173]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7174]="*“Rūpe kho, vaccha, appaccupekkhaṇā … pe … viññāṇe kho, vaccha, appaccupekkhaṇā … pe ….**“Vaccha, it is because of not scrutinizing form …”*";
P_HTM[7175]="*Paññāsamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7176]="*2. Samādhimūlakaṭhitisuttaṃ**51–54. Rūpaappaccakkhakammādisuttacatukka*";
P_HTM[7177]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7178]="*Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[7179]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7180]="*“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu, ko paccayo, yānimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**“What is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why these various misconceptions arise in the world? …”*";
P_HTM[7181]="*sassato lokoti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7182]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7183]="*“Rūpe kho, vaccha, appaccakkhakammā, rūpasamudaye appaccakkhakammā, rūpanirodhe appaccakkhakammā, rūpanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya appaccakkhakammā … pe ….**“Vaccha, it is because of not directly experiencing form …*";
P_HTM[7184]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7185]="*“Vedanāya kho, vaccha, appaccakkhakammā … pe … vedanānirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya appaccakkhakammā … pe ….**feeling …*";
P_HTM[7186]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7187]="*“Saññāya kho, vaccha, appaccakkhakammā … pe … saññānirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya appaccakkhakammā … pe ….**perception …*";
P_HTM[7188]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7189]="*“Saṅkhāresu kho, vaccha, appaccakkhakammā … pe … saṅkhāranirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya appaccakkhakammā … pe ….**choices …”*";
P_HTM[7190]="*Catupaññāsamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7191]="*3. Samādhimūlakavuṭṭhānasuttaṃ**Not Directly Experiencing Consciousness*";
P_HTM[7192]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7193]="*“Viññāṇe kho, vaccha, appaccakkhakammā, viññāṇasamudaye appaccakkhakammā, viññāṇanirodhe appaccakkhakammā, viññāṇanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya appaccakkhakammā;**“Vaccha, it is because of not directly experiencing consciousness, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation*";
P_HTM[7194]="*evamimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**that these various misconceptions arise in the world.*";
P_HTM[7195]="*sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7196]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vāti.* **";
P_HTM[7197]="*Ayaṃ kho, vaccha, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yānimāni anekavihitāni diṭṭhigatāni loke uppajjanti—**This is the cause, this is the reason.”*";
P_HTM[7198]="*sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā, antavā lokoti vā, anantavā lokoti vā, taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīranti vā, aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīranti vā, hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā, hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā, neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7199]="*Pañcapaññāsamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7200]="*Vacchagottavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[7201]="*Aññāṇā adassanā ceva,* **";
P_HTM[7202]="*Anabhisamayā ananubodhā;* **";
P_HTM[7203]="*Appaṭivedhā asallakkhaṇā,* **";
P_HTM[7204]="*Anupalakkhaṇena appaccupalakkhaṇā;* **";
P_HTM[7205]="*Asamapekkhaṇā appaccupekkhaṇā,* **";
P_HTM[7206]="*Appaccakkhakammanti.* **";
P_HTM[7207]="*Vacchagottasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses with Vacchagotta are completed.*";
P_HTM[7208]="*34. Jhānasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[7209]="*4. Samādhimūlakakallitasuttaṃ**Entering Immersion*";
P_HTM[7210]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7211]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7212]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7213]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in entering it.*";
P_HTM[7214]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo.**One meditator is not skilled in immersion but is skilled in entering it.*";
P_HTM[7215]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo.**One meditator is skilled neither in immersion nor in entering it.*";
P_HTM[7216]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo ca.**One meditator is skilled both in immersion and in entering it.*";
P_HTM[7217]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.**Of these, the meditator skilled in immersion and in entering it is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the four.*";
P_HTM[7218]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo tatra aggamakkhāyati;**From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee is said to be the best of these.*";
P_HTM[7219]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ samāpattikusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro cā”ti.**In the same way, the meditator skilled in immersion and entering it is the foremost, best, leading, highest, and finest of the four.”*";
P_HTM[7220]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7221]="*5. Samādhimūlakaārammaṇasuttaṃ**Remaining in Immersion*";
P_HTM[7222]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7223]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7224]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7225]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ ṭhitikusalo.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in remaining in it.*";
P_HTM[7226]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ ṭhitikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo.**One meditator is skilled in remaining in immersion but is not skilled in immersion.*";
P_HTM[7227]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ ṭhitikusalo.**One meditator is skilled neither in immersion nor in remaining in it.*";
P_HTM[7228]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ ṭhitikusalo ca.**One meditator is skilled both in immersion and in remaining in it.*";
P_HTM[7229]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ ṭhitikusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.**Of these, the meditator skilled in immersion and in remaining in it is the foremost, best, leading, highest, and finest of the four.*";
P_HTM[7230]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo tatra aggamakkhāyati;**From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee is said to be the best of these.*";
P_HTM[7231]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ ṭhitikusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro cā”ti.**In the same way, the meditator skilled in immersion and remaining in it is the foremost, best, leading, highest, and finest of the four.”*";
P_HTM[7232]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7233]="*6. Samādhimūlakagocarasuttaṃ**Emerging From Immersion*";
P_HTM[7234]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7235]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7236]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7237]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ vuṭṭhānakusalo.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in emerging from it. …”*";
P_HTM[7238]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ vuṭṭhānakusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7239]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ vuṭṭhānakusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7240]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ vuṭṭhānakusalo ca.* **";
P_HTM[7241]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ vuṭṭhānakusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.* **";
P_HTM[7242]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7243]="*pavaro cā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7244]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7245]="*7. Samādhimūlakaabhinīhārasuttaṃ**Gladdening for Immersion*";
P_HTM[7246]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7247]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7248]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7249]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ kallitakusalo.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in gladdening the mind for immersion. …”*";
P_HTM[7250]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ kallitakusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7251]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ kallitakusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7252]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ kallitakusalo ca.* **";
P_HTM[7253]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ kallitakusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.* **";
P_HTM[7254]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7255]="*pavaro cā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7256]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7257]="*8. Samādhimūlakasakkaccakārīsuttaṃ**Supports For Immersion*";
P_HTM[7258]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7259]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7260]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7261]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ ārammaṇakusalo.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in the supports for immersion. …”*";
P_HTM[7262]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ ārammaṇakusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7263]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ ārammaṇakusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7264]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ ārammaṇakusalo ca.* **";
P_HTM[7265]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ ārammaṇakusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.* **";
P_HTM[7266]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7267]="*pavaro cā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7268]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7269]="*9. Samādhimūlakasātaccakārīsuttaṃ**Meditation Subjects For Immersion*";
P_HTM[7270]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7271]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7272]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7273]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ gocarakusalo.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in the meditation subjects for immersion. …”*";
P_HTM[7274]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ gocarakusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7275]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ gocarakusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7276]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ gocarakusalo ca.* **";
P_HTM[7277]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ gocarakusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.* **";
P_HTM[7278]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7279]="*pavaro cā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7280]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7281]="*10. Samādhimūlakasappāyakārīsuttaṃ**Projecting the Mind Purified by Immersion*";
P_HTM[7282]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7283]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7284]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7285]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ abhinīhārakusalo.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in projecting the mind purified by immersion. …”*";
P_HTM[7286]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ abhinīhārakusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7287]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ abhinīhārakusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7288]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ abhinīhārakusalo ca.* **";
P_HTM[7289]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ abhinīhārakusalo ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.* **";
P_HTM[7290]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7291]="*pavaro cā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7292]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7293]="*11. Samāpattimūlakaṭhitisuttaṃ**Carefulness in Immersion*";
P_HTM[7294]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7295]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7296]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7297]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ sakkaccakārī.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in practicing carefully for it. …”*";
P_HTM[7298]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ sakkaccakārī hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7299]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ sakkaccakārī.* **";
P_HTM[7300]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ sakkaccakārī ca.* **";
P_HTM[7301]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti samādhismiṃ sakkaccakārī ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.* **";
P_HTM[7302]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7303]="*pavaro cā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7304]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7305]="*12. Samāpattimūlakavuṭṭhānasuttaṃ**Persistence in Immersion*";
P_HTM[7306]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7307]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7308]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7309]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in practicing persistently for it. …”*";
P_HTM[7310]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī hoti, na samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo.* **";
P_HTM[7311]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na ca samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī.* **";
P_HTM[7312]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī ca.* **";
P_HTM[7313]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo ca hoti, samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.* **";
P_HTM[7314]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7315]="*pavaro cā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7316]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7317]="*13. Samāpattimūlakakallitasuttaṃ**Conducive to Immersion*";
P_HTM[7318]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[7319]="*“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī.**“Mendicants, there are these four meditators.*";
P_HTM[7320]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[7321]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ samādhikusalo hoti, na samādhismiṃ sappāyakārī.**One meditator is skilled in immersion but not in doing what’s conducive to it. …”*";
